title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour and sugar; add milk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
After melting butter in baking dish, pour flour mixture into dish.
Drain off half of syrup from peaches, then pour into mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 1 hour.

title: orange slice-nut cookies(over 100 year old recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Beat eggs well; add brown sugar and mix well.
Add flour, orange slices and nuts.
Blend all together.
Grease 8 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
Measure wax paper to fit and grease. Spread cookie mixture on top.
Bake 20 minutes.
Invert pan and remove wax paper immediately.
Cool slightly; cut into squares and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: sausage on bread
directions: Brown sausage; crumble real small; drain.
Add Velveeta cheese and melt together.
Spread on bread.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch
greased pan.
While cake is still hot, punch holes over entire cake with fork.
Top cake with glaze.

title: chicken rice salad 1
directions: Brown rice slowly in skillet.
Add 2 3/4 cups hot water.
Stir in contents of flavoring packet.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Add olives, green pepper, celery and onions.
Cook until liquid is gone.
Chop artichokes, saving liquid.
Combine mayo and artichoke liquid.
Add curry, salt, pepper and garlic.
Combine with rice.
Add chicken.
Refrigerate.

title: blaze-of-glory chili
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole and cover. Microwave at 100% for 5 to 6 minutes. Stir once. Drain.
Stir in the kidney beans (drained), bay leaf, tomatoes (cut up), tomato soup, chili powder and pepper.
Cover and microwave on 50% for 20 minutes. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: punch slush
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil; let boil for 5 minutes. Cool.
Put bananas in blender and cover with some of the juices. Process until bananas are smooth.
To the cooled sugar water, add the bananas and all juices.
Mix well.
Pour into 6 equal containers and freeze.
Before serving, remove from freezer. Partially thaw.
Add 1 quart of ginger ale to each frozen portion and stir until slushy.
Six portions serve fifty people.

title: grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses, mixing well.
Stir flour and soda in and spices.
When thoroughly mixed, chill in refrigerator.
Roll dough into small balls (they will spread out during baking).
Bake at 325° for 6 minutes.

title: snow balls
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and egg yolk.
Fold in pecans and pineapple. Add egg whites.
Put mixture between three vanilla wafers.
Set overnight.
Ice with whipping cream and sprinkle with coconut.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together with a fork until crumbly and sprinkle over apples.
Pour 1/3 cup melted margarine over all.
Bake in a greased 6 x 10-inch baking dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Saute crawfish in butter for 5 minutes.
Remove crawfish. Saute vegetables about 10 minutes except peas and carrots.
Mix all ingredients and cook on medium heat for about 20 minutes.
Put in pie shell with top and bottom crust and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Mix in second three.
Crush 1 large bag Oreo cookies in blender or food processor, a few at a time.
When cookies are crushed they look like potting soil.
Set aside.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, peanut butter, confectioners sugar, milk and Cool Whip in bowl and mix well.
Spoon into pie shell.
Freeze for 1 to 2 hours, or until firm.
Keep in freezer until served. Can be served with thick chocolate syrup.
Serves 10.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
Cool.
Spear cake with a fork.
Heat milk, sugar and 1 package coconut until warm.
Pour over cake.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip and 1 package coconut.

title: nut bread
directions: Prepare mincemeat as for pie, but omit sugar.
Add brown sugar, shortening and water; let sit until cool.
Add 2 beaten eggs, flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Bake in 2 bread tins at 350° about an hour.
Turn out of pans and let cool.

title: chocolate-filled snowballs
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add flour and nuts; blend well. Chill dough about 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients with 4 cups of milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Finish filling container of ice cream mixer with milk.

title: pepper jelly
directions: In a large pot place the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes on very low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in Certo.
Bring pot back to heat and cook for 5 minutes.
Pour jelly into canning jars and seal.
Red or green food coloring may be added to mixture for coloring.
Yields about 4 (1/2-pint) jars.

title: creamy fettucini alfredo
directions: In large saucepan, combine cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, margarine and milk.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Stir in chicken and mushrooms.
Add fettucini.
Toss lightly.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off grease.
Add garlic, basil, 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough 1 hour.
Slice into 1/8-inch slices.
Line foil-lined 14-inch pizza pan with slices, overlapping edges slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Invert onto serving plate; carefully remove foil.
Invert to right side.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese layer.
Glaze with combined jelly or preserves with water; chill.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: maddie's vegetable pizza
directions: Create pizza crust by spreading crescent roll squares onto pan and pressing edges together.
Bake crust for 8 minutes at 400°. Cool pizza crust.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Boil rhubarb and sugar.
Add pineapple.
Boil 15 minutes. Remove from stove.
Add 2 packages of jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Return to stove and boil 5 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Also freezes well.

title: rosemary's baked beans
directions: Rinse and drain baked beans from the can.
Combine all ingredients (except beans) and mix well.
Put beans in a crock-pot and pour mixture over them; gently mix into beans.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Put in bowl in order given.
Mix when last item is added. Beat well.
Bake in a 375° oven.
Makes cupcakes or loaf.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Heat oven
Toss peeled (or not) potato wedges in a mixture
of remaining ingredients.	Bake on foil covered cookie sheet until tender.
Broil 2 minutes until browned.

title: jambalaya
directions: In
a
large saucepan, melt margarine and saute sausage and ham until lightly browned.	Stir in flour.	Add scallions, green pepper
and
garlic and saute until vegetables are soft. Stir
in tomatoes,
bay
leaf, thyme, pepper, broth, chicken, rice and shrimp.
The liquid in the pot should just cover the contents. Bring to a boil, lower heat until simmering.
Cover the pot
and cook
until
all
liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Season with salt;	remove bay leaf and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: white sauce ii
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, then add flour, stirring until mixture becomes foamy, but not brown.
Add milk.
Continue stirring to insure smoothness.
Cook until thickened.
Season. This sauce is used in cream soups and scalloped dishes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix (at room temperature) the cream cheese.
Add drained pineapple, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Place on aluminum foil and form into a ball.
Place in freezer until firm.
Remove from freezer and roll ball in the 1 1/2 cups pecan halves until ball is covered with nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix well.
Chill until this can be rolled into a ball.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a large saucepan over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Mixture will be thin and clear.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in corn flakes until coated.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in mixture. Smooth out the top and let set until cool.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put chicken breasts in a boiler and salt and pepper.
Add water to pan, about an inch over the chicken breasts.
Boil until done. Take chicken out of broth and debone.
Add deboned chicken to broth.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all of the filling ingredients.
Spread on tortillas; roll up tortillas.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap, twisting ends. Refrigerate for several hours.
Unwrap and slice.

title: tuna cheese buns
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and put on hamburger buns.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: uncooked strawberry jam
directions: Wash and crush berries.
Mix berries and sugar.
Let stand 20 minutes; stir occasionally.
Dissolve Sure-Jell in water and boil 1 minute.
Add to fruit and sugar.
Stir 2 minutes.
Put in glasses and let stand until it gels.
Seal and freeze.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add cornstarch, salt, vanilla and sugar.
Mix well and add milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Layer sliced bananas, vanilla wafers and pudding filling.

title: pepper steak
directions: May use stir-fry style meat, since it works well.
Brown steak in its own liquid, plus enough oil so as not to stick.
Do not drain, but add onion, pepper, pimentos, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Brown a few minutes.
Mix flour with water; add to beef.
This will thicken.
Keep stirred from bottom of pan; keep adding water to keep enough liquid for gravy.
Salt to taste.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, nuts and cocoa in large bowl.
Add milk and oil, stirring well.
Spoon into an ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Combine brown sugar and 1 tablespoon cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour water over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.
Can be doubled easily.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, sour cream, vanilla and cinnamon together. Fill pie crust 3/4 full of rhubarb.
Pour mixture over.
Bake at 425°
for 15 minutes.
Continue baking at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, lemon juice, vanilla and bananas.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately 1/3 cup at a time with sour cream to creamed mixture until well blended.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour or 2 loaves; 3 small
loaves at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: roast lamb(arni psito)
directions: Cut incisions in meat and fill with garlic mixed with salt and pepper.
Rub leg of lamb with lemon juice, oregano and additional salt and pepper.
Place in roasting pan with water and top with butter.
Bake in hot oven (450°) until browned, then lower heat to 350°, cover and bake until done.
When meat is half cooked, peeled and quartered potatoes may be placed in the roasting pan around the lamb.
Uncover during last minutes of baking to brown meat and potatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: maple's chicken and rice
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and bake in a casserole (covered) for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and
dice potatoes.
Cook potatoes with salt.
Mix together
all
ingredients.
Additional mayonnaise and mustard can be used if desired.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: cooked cucumbers
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers into thick slices or quarters.
Heat water and salt to boiling; add cucumbers.
Cover pan tightly to prevent escape of steam and heat again to boiling.
Reduce heat at once and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
(Makes about 4 cups cooked.)
To serve, season with pepper and butter.
Serves 6 to 8. Optional:
Top with Hollandaise Sauce.

title: lipton onion burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape into 8 patties.
Grill or broil until done.
Makes about 8 servings.
tags: Recipe Secrets beefy onion soup mix

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Cook until sugar melts. Take off burner and add peanut butter.
Add to 8 cups Rice Krispies and stir to coat.	Pour in a greased pan while warm and sprinkle small bag of butterscotch chips and semi-sweet chips and allow to melt into candy bar cookies.
Spread when melted.	Cut into bar cookies.

title: easy oven beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a large ovenproof bowl or pan.
Pour 1 can golden mushroom soup mixed with 1/2 can water over the vegetable mixture.
Put tight fitting lid over bowl.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake 3 to 3 1/2 hours at 325°.
Stir well and serve.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Take off stove and add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth; add Rice Krispies.
Mix well. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: bourbon chicken
directions: Mix marinade. Spread chicken in a single layer in shallow pan and cover with marinade. The longer it marinates, the better the flavor. Preheat oven to 350°. Bake for 45 minutes. This recipe can be grilled also.

title: brownies
directions: Mix by hand and bake for 20 minutes at 375° in an 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg and rest of ingredients. Beat until well mixed.
Put into long loaf pan.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: best yet broccoli bake
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in margarine for 5 minutes. Add broccoli and cover. Cook until tender, about 20 minutes. Place in buttered baking dish. Top with remaining ingredients mixed together. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crumb coated chicken(microwave)
directions: In shallow dish, place crumbs.
Coat chicken with crumbs, then in egg mixture (remaining ingredients); then in crumbs again.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop 1/2 c. raw cranberries. Add sugar and let stand overnight. Dissolve jello in boiling water, add orange rind, orange juice, crushed pineapple and chopped celery. When partially set fold in cranberries and pour in ring mold and let set.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix the sugar and flour and add vinegar and water; cook until thick.
Add salt and butter, then diced beets and reheat before serving.

title: silly cabbage
directions: Start cabbage, bell pepper, onion and tomatoes to cook in 1 1/2 cups water. Add margarine and Tabasco sauce. Very good dish.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in the order given in a dish that can be used in a microwave.
Microwave on High until it bubbles.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix well.
Put into buttered dish and top with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Stew chicken in salted water until tender, cool and pull apart.
Remove any bones.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Place broccoli in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Cover with chicken.
Mix soups together with mayonnaise and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, until cheese is bubbly and browning.

title: hot wassail punch
directions: Puncture orange slices with cloves (or tie in simmer bag).
Mix all ingredients in a large pot; bring to a boil.
Let simmer until ready to serve.
(Remove spices if punch is to simmer for a long time.)
This punch can be refrigerated after making and allowed to cool.
Just pour into a mug and heat in the microwave for a quick treat.

title: mike's bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add eggs.
Add vegetable oil and buttermilk.
Put
into muffin pans and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.
You can double recipe.

title: texas rotel
directions: In crock-pot melt cream cheese; add sausage and remaining ingredients
and
cook
on
low.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: french oven beef stew
directions: In 2 1/2-quart casserole, place beef and vegetables.
Sprinkle sugar, tapioca and basil over and pour V-8 juice over.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Cut up potatoes and add.
Bake another hour; stir occasionally.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Delicious over ice cream and other desserts.

title: waldorf cake
directions: Mix sugar and salad dressing; add water and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes in Bundt or tubular pan.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Precook cauliflower and carrots 5 minutes in boiling water. Drain. Layer cauliflower and carrots in a casserole dish. Top with soup. Season lightly with salt and pepper. Sprinkle top with croutons (cheese is optional). Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: soft enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meats and onion in large skillet. Season to taste.
Drain.
Add tomatoes with green chilies, chili powder, cumin and oregano.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Place 3 to 4 tablespoons of meat mixture in center of each tortilla.
Fold tortilla to make roll.
Fold ends down.
Place seam side down in a large ungreased baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining meat mixture on top of rolled enchiladas.
Combine cream of chicken soup and Velveeta cheese in medium saucepan.
Heat until cheese melts. Stir constantly.
Pour over enchiladas.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until bubbly.
May be frozen.

title: crab stuffed potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; scoop out potatoes, reserving shells.
Combine potatoes, milk, margarine, salt and pepper in bowl; whip until fluffy.
Add onion, cheese and crab meat; mix well.
Spoon into shell.
Place on baking sheet; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute 1/2 pound fresh mushrooms (sliced) and 1 large onion (chopped) in 3 tablespoons butter.	Cut 2 pound sirloin or beef tenderloin in 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick pieces; coat meat in flour and brown in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Dilute to 2 cups, 1 can beef bouillon and add to meat mixture.	Simmer 1 1/4 hours, stirring once in a while.
Add mushrooms and onion mixture and 1 cup sour cream.
Add 2 tablespoons sherry.

title: angel food cake
directions: Slice cake in half; add drained pineapple to bottom half and 3/4 of prepared pudding on top of pineapple.
Next, lay top half of cake and then rest of pudding.
Cover all over with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Heat to boiling and pour over cabbage.
Refrigerate 12 hours. Improves with age.
Slaw will keep at least one week.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In skillet, melt oleo.
Add celery and stir over medium-high heat until crisp and tender.
Stir in soup, milk, onion powder, thyme and pepper and mix well.
Stir in vegetables and chicken; heat through.
Spoon into 12 x 18-inch baking dish.
Make Bisquick biscuits and place on top.

title: pudding torte
directions: Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: best pie crust ever
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add Crisco; mix well with pastry knife. Beat egg in a 1-cup measuring cup filled with water.
Stir.
Mix well with dry ingredients.
Makes 4 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in boiling salted water 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Save 1/4 cup liquid.
Alternate layers of vegetables with cheese in dish.
Pour milk, vegetable liquid, salt and pepper over vegetables.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: apple dump dessert
directions: Spread apple pie mix on the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Evenly distribute dry cake mix over filling.
Pour melted butter over dry cake mix.
Sprinkle pecan chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: ez white chili
directions: In pan heat chicken.
Add salsa, beans and broth and heat until hot.
Place in bowls.
Add spoonful of sour cream and sprinkle with cheese.

title: vegetable and shrimp salad
directions: Cook and cool pasta.
Steam vegetables until crisp-tender. Put oil, lemon juice, dry salad dressing mix and horseradish in a jar and shake well.
Toss with pasta and vegetables.
Refrigerate. Best to chill overnight.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together soft shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Mix all together and form into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in a mixture of sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Put yeast in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients as given. Grease muffin pan.
Put 1 tablespoon of dough in each.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Put remaining dough in refrigerator.
Do not cover tightly!

title: easter lilies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until very thick.
Add water.
Sift dry ingredients
together
and
fold
gently
into
egg-sugar mixture. Grease inexpensive saucers and dust with flour.
Add dough to each saucer
and
bake
for 10 minutes at 350°.
Fold bottoms and hold firmly with knife until cool.

title: mock pierogies
directions: In covered frying pan, melt margarine.
Add chopped onions and simmer until tender.
Add drained sauerkraut and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni and mix well.
Put in baking bowl, cover and bake 20 minutes at 375° to 400°.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine peas, onion, green pepper and garlic; toss lightly. Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over pea mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Remove garlic before serving.
Yield 6 to 8 servings.

title: western skillet rice
directions: In medium skillet brown meat; drain.
Stir in Lipton onion soup, water, cooked rice, tomatoes and peas.
Simmer covered 30 minutes, then top with cheese.
Cheese will melt.
Enjoy!

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Dissolve jello into 2 cups boiling water (use 8 x 12-inch square dish).
Allow jello to almost set, then add drained, crushed pineapple.
Return to refrigerator until completely congealed.

title: honey mustard pork tenderloin
directions: Combine all ingredients except the meat.
Cover meat with sauce.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until meat thermometer reaches 155°.
Serves 2.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on box.
When almost congealed, add other ingredients and continue to congeal until ready to serve.

title: chili-tamale dip
directions: Mix well and cook in double boiler until cheese melts.
Serve with Doritos.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning, mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Layer refried beans, mixture and salsa sauce in a casserole dish; sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese and garnish with olives. Microwave (High) for seven minutes.

title: plastic pickles
directions: Soak in lime water for 11 or 12 hours.
Wash in cold water. Soak cucumbers in salt water for 4 hours.
Drain.
Soak in clear water for 2 hours.
Bring to boil in alum water.
Wash in hot water.
Boil for 30 minutes in vinegar and spices mixture.
Let stand overnight.
Can.

title: florentine turkey noodle casserole
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cornstarch until blended.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth. Stir in broth, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
In 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish, pour 1 cup of the sauce to cover bottom. Layer 2 1/4 cups noodles, spinach, turkey and 1 cup cheese.
Top with remaining noodles.
Pour sauce over noodles.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Great for holiday leftover turkey!

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Beat pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line pan (9 x 13-inch) with graham crackers. Spread 1/2 pudding over crackers. Repeat.
End with graham crackers on top.

title: caramels
directions: Combine all ingredients except for 1 cup of cream and 1/3 cup butter.
Bring to a boil; slowly add the other cup of cream so that the mixture continues to boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup real butter one teaspoon at a time.
Cook until candy thermometer reads 240°.
Take off heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour into a 9-inch square pan and let stand 2 hours.
Cut into 1/2-inch squares and wrap in Saran Wrap.

title: korean chicken and cashews
directions: In Microwave:
In oblong baking dish, heat oil 2 1/2 to 3 minutes on High.
Combine chicken, garlic, soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and ginger.
Add to dish; heat 3 to 4 minutes on High, stirring twice.
Add green pepper and cashews; cook, covered, 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes on High, until chicken and green pepper are tender, stirring once.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: uncooked fudge
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in a saucepan, melting some of the butter first.
Pour in the cream and vanilla.
While beating with an electric mixer, add the sugar gradually, then the egg and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper in bite size pieces.
Allow to cool at least 12 hours.

title: 7 layer wonders
directions: Mix crumbs and melted oleo.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with a layer of chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, nuts and coconut.
Cover with sweetened milk.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 36 servings.

title: pistachio and rum pudding cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt or tube pan.
Place nuts in the bottom, all around the ring.
Empty cake mix and pudding mix into a bowl.
Add eggs, oil and milk.
Beat well until batter is smooth and thick.
Pour batter into the cake pan and bake for 1 hour until cake is a beautiful brown.
Remove from oven and let cool. Remove the cake and turn it upside-down onto a cake plate or stand.
Poke several holes into the top with a toothpick.
Prepare Rum Glaze.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir together eggs, sugar, corn syrup, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: spring vegetable casserole
directions: To cook vegetables, bring 1-inch of water to a boil in a 2-quart saucepan over high heat. Add potatoes. Cover and return to a boil. Reduce heat to a low. Simmer until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes. Drain and set aside. Repeat cooking process with the cauliflower, carrots and asparagus, cooking separately, just until crisp-tender.

title: lee's steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into small pieces.
Flour and fry brown on both sides.
Mix gravy mix according to directions on package.
Let set while steak is frying.
Slice up onions.
Put onions in bottom of baking pan.
Lay steak on top of onions.
Stir gravy mix good and pour over steak.
Cover pan and put in oven at 375° and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: squash and green chili casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in water until tender.
Drain and mash. Season with butter, salt and pepper. Pour into large bowl.
Add drained chilies and eggs.
Butter a 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Cover bottom with cheese. Spread squash mixture on top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour in pan of hot water. Ten minutes before taking out of oven, poke 4 holes in mixture so cheese will rise.

title: hunky mess
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large skillet.
Simmer over medium heat until flavors mix and green pepper is tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: cheese capers
directions: Thinly slice onions, including green part. Drain the olives, pimento and capers well, then chop.
Combine ingredients and spread on English muffins. Cut into quarters. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbling.
Makes 48 appetizers.
May be refrigerated for 24 hours or frozen.
Bring to room temperature before baking.

title: hot dogs and potatoes
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add potatoes and tomatoes plus a dash of salt, pepper and paprika. Cover with water.
Cover pot and cook until potatoes are done.
Add cut up hot dogs and cook for 15 more minutes.

title: texas pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Arrange in bottom of pan.
Place 1 onion slice and 1 pepper slice on top of each chop.
Pour rice around in pan.
Spoon the mixture of tomato soup, water, vinegar and mustard over all and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: becky's barbecue
directions: Line bottom of pan with Crisco oil.
Brown ground chuck.
Add onion and brown a little more.
Add tomato soup.
Add cinnamon and brown sugar to taste.
Serve on hamburger buns with cole slaw or cheese.

title: steak stir-fry
directions: Fill pan 3/4 full of water. Mix ingredients. Cook until most of the water is gone.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Layer fruit in glass bowl, beginning with grapes, then bananas, peaches, raspberries, oranges and kiwi.
Pour orange juice over salad and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Keep salad well chilled until ready to serve.
Great over pound cake!

title: my favorite punch
directions: Mix gelatin in 4 cups water.
Mix sugar in other 4 cups water and bring
to
a
boil until sugar is dissolved.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Freeze until ready to
use in plastic container.
When ready to use, mix ginger ale and serve.	Makes 40 servings.
Can make a ring with part of the mixture to put in punch bowl, too!

title: chocolate chip blonde brownies(a campbell favorite!)
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix the shortening, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Place in greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake approximately 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: wiener water soup
directions: Combine wieners and water in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil until wieners are cooked.
Throw the wieners in the garbage. Serve soup.
Serves 3.

title: mom's hot dog relish
directions: Grind vegetables. Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight. Combine other ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: Divide berries into 2 equal portions.
In a heavy saucepan, mash half of berries.
Add 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice and cook over low heat, blending well until thick and translucent. Remove from heat and cool.
In a separate bowl, combine cream cheese, remaining 1/3 cup sugar, orange peel, orange juice and half and half.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Spread cream cheese mixture smoothly and evenly into pie shell.
Arrange whole berries over cream cheese mixture and cover with the cooled strawberry glaze.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
If desired, serve with dollops of lightly sweetened whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: saucy kielbasa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan and simmer for 1 hour or longer, depending on how candied you want it.
Serve as an hor d'oeuvre with toothpicks.
Can be served in a chafing dish.

title: apple pie
directions: Put sliced apples in pastry shell.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice over apples.
I like to put about 2 tablespoons of margarine dotted over this.

title: spiced sweet potatoe cake
directions: Pierce sweet potatoes with fork. Microwave on high until very tender, about 8 minutes per side. Cool, peel and mash sweet potatoes. Position rack in center of oven; preheat to 325°. Spray 12 cup bundt pan with nonstick spray, then generously butter pan. Sift flour, cinnamon, ginger, baking powder, baking soda and salt into medium bowl. Measure enough mashed potatoes to equal 2 cups. Transfer to large bowl. Add sugar and oil to potatoes, using electric mixer, beat until smooth. Add eggs, 2 at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour mixture; beat just until blended. Beat in vanilla. Transfer batter to prepared pan.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together eggs, pumpkin and oil; set aside.
Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and sugar.
Combine with first mixture.
Grease and flour a cookie sheet.
Spread mixture on sheet and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes; let cool and spread on topping.
Add raisins and nuts, if desired.

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter or oleo and sugar together. Beat in milk, orange juice and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Blend well with sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts and cranberries.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, oleo, vanilla, sugar, eggs and milk.
Mix well and pour into baking dish.

title: oven barbecued chicken wings
directions: Cut off small wing tips of each chicken wing and discard.
Cut remaining wings into 2 parts.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and the oil.
Set aside.

title: cider punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Flavor is improved if mixture is refrigerated for 1 to 2 days.
Reheat to serve.
Makes about 14 servings.

title: chicken club brunch ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In 1 qt. bowl combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Add parsley and onion to mayonnaise mixture; mix well.
In 2 qt. bowl, flake chicken.
Add bacon, 3/4 cup of the cheese and 1/3 cup of mayonnaise mixture; mix well. Unroll crescent dough; separate into 16 triangles.
Arrange triangles in a circle on 13 in. cooking stone or pizza pan with wide ends of triangles overlapping in the center and points toward the outside.
(There should be a 5 in. diameter opening in center.)
Scoop chicken mixture evenly onto widest end of each triangle.
Bring outside points of triangles up over filling and tuck under wide ends of dough at center of rind.
(Filling will not be completely covered.)
Cut sliced tomatoes in half.
Place one tomato half over filling between openings of ring.
Bake 20 - 25 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Cut top off bell pepper, remove membranes and seeds.
Fill with remaining mayonnaise mixture (you can use a small bowl in place of bell pepper); place in center of ring.
Arrange lettuce around pepper or bowl.
Cut into 8 equal slices and serve.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Break half of the angel food cake into pieces and over a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend 1 stick of margarine, 4 egg yolks and 2 cups of confectioners sugar.
Fork Cool Whip into the mixture and layer the mixture over pieces of angel food cake.
Layer half of the crushed Butterfinger candy bars over the Cool Whip mixture. Repeat 3 layers again.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: pork with green pepper and pineapple
directions: Slice pork thinly (this is easiest when meat is partly frozen).
Combine soy sauce and 1 tablespoon cornstarch in a bowl. Marinate pork in this mixture and set aside.
Mix remaining cornstarch with sugar and 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Set aside. Heat oil in a large skillet or wok.
Add pork to the skillet and stir-fry until done.
Add pineapple juice mixture to meat and blend thoroughly.
Set aside.
Stir-fry green pepper, carrots and pineapple juice for about 3 minutes.
Blend thoroughly with other ingredients.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans and salt pork until almost done.
Stir in the next ten ingredients and continue to cook until done.
Brown sausage and drain.
Add to beans and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: shrimp primavera
directions: Boil shrimp in shell until pink (approximately 2 to 3 minutes). Shell shrimp and set aside.
Boil pasta; set aside.
Saute garlic in oil; add vegetables.
Cook until tender, yet firm.
Combine shrimp, pasta and sauteed vegetables in large bowl.
Garnish with tomatoes.
Serve at room temperature, or cold.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion.
Drain part of liquid from beans. Mix salt, vinegar and brown sugar.
Add bean mixture to meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or cook in crock-pot 7 hours on low.

title: butterscotch coconut pie
directions: Put chips and coconut in bottom of the two crusts.
Mix the remaining ingredients together by hand.
Pour half of the mixture over the chips and coconut in each crust.
Cook at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Beat ingredients together, except for vanilla wafers.
Drop a vanilla wafer in 24 Reynolds baking cups.
Top 3/4 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely. Top with Cool Whip and a teaspoon of cherry pie filling.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: baked eye of round with rosemary
directions: Leave meat out of refrigerator prior to cooking; needs to be room temperature.
Leave fat side up when baking.
Season meat 2 days before cooking.
Mix all ingredients together; rub surface of meat with mixture.
Wrap tightly in aluminum foil and refrigerate. Prior to cooking, remove from refrigerator early enough for it to get to room temperature.
Brown meat in shortening.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake at 325° to desired doneness.
For rare, bake 5 minutes per pound; for medium, bake 20 minutes per pound and for well, bake 22 minutes per pound.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni 6 minutes; drain and add cheese, soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken cheese chowder
directions: In a large pan, cook carrots and onion in butter until tender. Blend in flour; add milk and broth.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in chicken, wine, celery seed and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat well.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese; layer mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture and layer with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: amish sugar cream pie
directions: Combine half and half and sugar in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Stir occasionally.
Meanwhile, combine brown sugar and cornstarch in another saucepan.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour hot half and half mixture into brown sugar mixture a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Add butter. Return to stove.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes or until thickened. Simmer 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Mix with Crisco. Add buttermilk and mix well. Knead a few times. Cut and bake at 450 for 15 - 20 minutes.

title: mozzarella sticks
directions: Slice frozen bread as thin as possible. Melt butter, add flour and add heated milk to butter and flour mixture. Stir with wire whisk until lumps disappear. Add cheese, horseradish, and bouillon cube. Cook over low heat ten minutes. Cool.
Spread mixture on bread slices and roll up. Fry in 350° fat until golden brown.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix onions, green chilies, stewed tomatoes, egg and oatmeal together.
Mix in hamburger meat until all ingredients are combined.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: chicken - ham roll-up
directions: Place chicken breasts on ham slices.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Cover with Durkee spread and soup.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix and store in tightly sealed container.
To serve, stir 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of mix into each cup of boiling water.

title: greta's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place chicken breasts in pan and pepper. Top with sliced mushrooms.
Mix soup, sour cream and wine.
Pour evenly over chicken and mushrooms.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake about 45 minutes or until done. Serve over choice of rice.
Makes 6 to 10 servings.

title: vegetable toss
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lettuce and croutons.
Toss to blend.
Arrange on lettuce leaves.
Top with croutons. Makes 6 servings.

title: savoy eggs
directions: Peel hard-boiled eggs, slice cleanly in half and remove yolks. Mash yolks and stir into yogurt, mayonnaise and mustard mixture blending well. Mound mixture into egg white halves and garnish with paprika and olives.

title: cafe special
directions: Saute chicken with butter, add brandy, mustard seed & cream. Serve on rice or noodles.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: strawberry pie with graham cracker crust
directions: Mix cornstarch and water together.
Heat slowly.
Bring to a boil and cook until thick.
Add gelatin and Sweet 'N Low packets. Stir to dissolve completely.
Fold in strawberries, then pour into graham cracker crust and chill until serving time.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix each ingredient in the order listed, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into a 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: garden vegetable salad
directions: Chill vegetables and olives in large bowl.
Combine yogurt, chili sauce, lemon juice and salt.
Just before serving, toss yogurt dressing with vegetables.
Line serving bowl with lettuce leaves and spoon salad into center.
Yields 6 servings, 83 calories each.

title: beef-cheese spread
directions: Chop dried beef fine and mix with cream cheese, onion and pepper.
Form into desired shape and serve with crackers.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in shaker and shake well.
Can be refrigerated.
This dressing works well with this combination of ingredients: Torn spinach, sliced purple onions, diced boiled eggs, fried and crumbled bacon and cherry tomatoes.

title: hot almond crab spread
directions: Soften cheese and combine with milk.
Add crab, onions, horseradish and pepper and mix well.
Place in ovenproof dish. Cover with almonds.

title: white holiday cake
directions: Dredge raisins and pecans in flour.
Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add one egg at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and peanut butter; add sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, blending thoroughly.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven; immediately place unwrapped kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so that the cookie cracks around the edge.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: christmas pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick.
Remove from heat and add next 3 ingredients.
Put mixture into pie crusts.
Chill. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: sausage biscuit bites
directions: Cook sausage in skillet; drain well and set aside.
Combine next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add yeast mixture to buttermilk, stirring well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened. Knead in sausage.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Don't add water to dressing mix. Make balls the size of walnuts and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with Ranch dressing dip.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Drain juice from oranges; mix with pudding mix.
Cook this mixture until thickened over low heat.
Slice cookie dough thin and place, overlapping, on pizza pan.
Press dough flat; bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: fried rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed on box.
Cook bacon until crisp, reserving 1/2 cup grease.
Saute bell pepper and onions in bacon grease.
Add salt, garlic salt (if desired), pepper and soy sauce.
Beat eggs together and pour into mixture and scramble. Pour into rice and mix together.
Crumble bacon and mix.
Makes a large dish.

title: cinnamon stick bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Mix in egg yolk.
Add flour, cinnamon and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread dough in a greased jelly roll pan. Spread slightly beaten egg white over top of dough.
Sprinkle with sugar and pecans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Remove and slice immediately into bars.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
When ready to serve, add carbonated water.
Pour this over ice in a large punch bowl.
Serves 40 to 45.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add shortening to flour mixture. Mix with fork or pastry cutter until small like peas.
In separate bowl beat with fork, water, vinegar and egg.
Add mixture to flour mixture.
Cover hands with flour and shape into ball.
Refrigerate at least 1/2 hour before rolling out.
Separate into 4 balls. This makes 4 crusts or 2 pies.
This dough can also be frozen up to 2 months.
Eat and enjoy pie.

title: corn muffins
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Combine buttermilk, egg whites and oil.
Stir into dry mixture just to moisten.
Fold in corn.
Bake in muffin cups at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Cook ingredients together until a few drops will form a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat; cool.
When candy is slightly warm, beat until it begins to get creamy, then pour into buttered pan or pour on a damp cloth and shape into a roll.
When firm, cut into small pieces.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
A cast-iron skillet works best.
Add some oil to lightly cover bottom.
Get hot. Drop 1 tablespoon of batter in three areas of skillet.
Will cook like pancakes.
When bubbles form and edges turn brown, flip with a spatula.
Brown on that side.
Take up.
Add more oil for next three cornbread. Continue until done.
Makes about 21 circles.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Roll crescents out thin.
Mix chicken, cream cheese, onion and celery together.
Place 1 or 2 Tbsp. of chicken mixture in center of large end of rolls.
Roll up and tuck under. Dip bundles in melted butter and roll in Pepperidge Farms stuffing.

title: vegetable marinade salad
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl and marinate with dressing and seasoning.
Cover and keep in refrigerator overnight.

title: puffy french toast
directions: Combine milk, egg and biscuit mix in bowl.
Cut each bread slice in half diagonally and dip in batter, coating completely. Heat shortening in skillet.
Saute bread until golden brown and puffy, about 3 minutes on each side.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onions, drain. Mix Hidden Valley ranch mix and taco seasoning into meat. Then, without draining, add all of the other ingredients. Simmer 1 hour. This is delicious served with Baked Tostitos chips. Of course that does add a few calories. Makes 12 one cup servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: In large glass bowl or punch bowl, crumble angel food cake to pieces.
Put a layer in bottom of bowl.
Mix vanilla pudding by directions on box.
Wash and hull strawberries.
Cut them up in halves.
Layer cake pieces, pudding mix, strawberries, then Cool Whip, until all are mixed.
Be sure Cool Whip is on top.
Keep 1 strawberry for decoration.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar; crumble.
Prepare instant pudding according to package directions.
Spread most of crumbles on bottom of baked pie shell.
Pour pudding (prepared according to directions) over crumbles.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with remaining crumbles on top of Cool Whip.
Chill 1 hour.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine; add onion, garlic and tarragon and cook for 1 minute.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and add to the pan and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Add wine, then return chicken and cook on the uncooked side.
Cook chicken 3 minutes; remove from pan again.
Mix bouillon, water, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard; add cornstarch. Add sauce, chicken and carrots to pan and cook for 5 minutes, covered over low heat.
Serve with rice.

title: fat-free cholesterol-free carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 10-cup fluted tube pan with no stick spray.
In large bowl, mix flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt.
In medium bowl with wire whisk, beat brown sugar, egg substitute, applesauce and vanilla until smooth.
Stir egg substitute mixture, shredded carrots, pineapple with its juice and walnuts into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Pour batter into tube pan.
Bake 65 minutes.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan.
To serve, sprinkle top of cake lightly with confectioners sugar.
Makes 16 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Mix ingredients in gallon container.
Fill with water.
Freeze until slushy.

title: fruit chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in large Dutch oven.
Bring to boil and cook, uncovered, over low heat 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Chill.
Yields 4 cups.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix shortening and peanut butter with a wooden spoon.
Add both kinds of sugar.
Stir until mixed.
Stir in eggs and vanilla until mixed.
Add flour, soda and salt; stir until well mixed.
(You may need to use your hands.)
Form dough into balls and roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and press lightly with a fork to form crisscross pattern. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: macaroni-pineapple toss
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Rinse with cold water. Toss with remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Place oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot.

Add chopped pepper and onion. Cook 3 minutes, stirring often. Add cumin and cook 1 minute, stirring often. Add chicken and tomato. Cook 3 minutes, stirring often. Stir in minced cilantro, salt and ground pepper.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk and cook until soft ball.
Add marshmallow cream and stir in until melted. Add nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: bonbon's
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Dip in melted chocolate chips and paraffin.

title: aunt sue's stuffed dates
directions: Gradually add 4 cups of the sugar to milk, blending well. Mix in salt and extracts.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup sugar on board and knead fondant until smooth and creamy, working in the sugar.
Wrap in aluminum foil and let ripen 24 hours in refrigerator.
Stuff dates, top with walnut halves, coconut or bits of candied cherries.
Makes enough fondant to fill 9 to 10 dozen dates.

title: microwave chili bean dip
directions: Place chili in container of blender. Cover and process until smooth.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart microproof bowl. Add cheese and hot pepper sauce. Cook on 50 (Simmer) for 4 to 7 minutes
or until cheese is melted, stirring once during cooking time. Blend well. Serve with corn or tortilla chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Fill 1/2 the pie shell with softened ice cream.
Cover with a layer of sprinkles.
Fill pie shell to top with softened ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place in freezer until hardened. Serves 8.

title: ruth's chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add egg yolks and Pet milk. Cook over low heat until thick.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and vanilla.
Place in ready baked pie shell.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
In mixing bowl, cream shortening and add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with combined orange juice and rind, beginning and ending with dry ingredients and mixing well after each addition.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake about 1 hour or until pick stuck in center comes out clean.
Our Thanksgiving favorite!

title: mini sausage quiches
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese in medium bowl until creamy; blend in flour.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll into 24 (1-inch) balls and press each into mini muffin cup.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla. Mix well. Add dry ingredients, raisins, pecans and applesauce. Pour into greased muffin tins, filling cups about 2/3 full. Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes. Yields 1 dozen muffins.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Precook lima beans, carrots, onions and celery in microwave for 10 minutes.
(Cook per your microwave instructions).
Cut up the celery and carrots and onion and mix all ingredients together. Cook about 45 minutes.
Total calories = 2488.
Total fat = 3.7 grams.
Makes 14 cups. 2 cups = 356 calories, .6 grams fat.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining two ingredients.
Spoon over individual servings of ice cream.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown chuck and onion.
Pour into greased quiche dish, stirring in seasoning mix.
Add chilies.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick and pour in.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more until knife comes out clean, then top with sour cream, tomatoes and lettuce.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix with fork until it looks like thin cream, then add 2 cups flour.
Divide dough and roll out between 2 pieces of wax paper. (This crust never fails.)

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted butter and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Beat powdered sugar, vanilla, butter and egg until creamy; spread on crumbs. Refrigerate at least 20 minutes.
Drain pineapple; spread on sugar mixture.
Slice bananas on top (can sprinkle lemon juice to prevent darkening).
Spread Cool Whip over all.
Sprinkle on nuts and put pieces of cherries over top.

title: wassail punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for two hours.
Serve hot.
May be stored in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients
together well except 1 cup chopped pecans. Roll cheese ball in pecans. May make 1 very large or 2 small. Wrap in
Saran
Wrap
and chill overnight before eating with your favorite crackers.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture with milk.
Chill one hour.
Roll out on board 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Brush with slightly beaten egg white and dip brushed side with sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese au vin
directions: Cook macaroni, drain in colander and wash with cold water. Grease casserole with olive oil, including sides and bottom.
This casserole is made in layers.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, pineapple and peach.
Place on bed of lettuce. Mix mayo and cream.
Pour over chicken and fruit.
Garnish.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Brush the eggplant slices with thin layer of oil.
Broil until lightly browned on both sides, about 2 minutes per side.
Pour approximately 1/3 of the tomato sauce into bottom of a 9 x 9-inch square baking dish.
Add a layer of eggplant and top with some tomato sauce, chopped parsley, oregano and 1 tablespoon of Parmesan cheese.
Repeat the process to make a second layer, ending with Parmesan cheese.
Top casserole sprinkling shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: ruth's jam cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Add buttermilk, jam, spices and cocoa.
Add flour and the 1/2 cup water containing soda.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: creamy tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
In a small bowl, mix soup, milk, onion and peas or carrots.
In a casserole dish, place half of the macaroni, then pour 1/2 the soup mixture and a layer of cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine eggs, onion, celery, salt, beans, pepper and water. Cook a little.
Heat can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of water. Mix all together.
Grate 1 cup of Cheddar cheese over top.
Crush 1 cup cracker crumbs and sprinkle over top.

title: two egg treasure cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: double chocolate gooey butter cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease 9 x 3 baking pan. In large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 egg and stick melted butter. Stir until well blended. Pat mixture into pan and set aside.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients (sift together) and add beaten eggs and oil to dry mixture and juice.
Then add fruit and nuts.
Bake in a loaf pan in a 300° oven for 45 minutes.
This makes 18 slices, each of which equals 1 fat, 1 bread and 1/2 fruit.

title: gumdrop bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add beaten eggs; beat together. Add flour, salt, oats, baking powder, baking soda, coconut, gumdrops and vanilla; mix all together.
Press into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, sift icing sugar over top.
Cut into 36 squares.

title: granola
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly, and bake in shallow pans at 275° until coconut is lightly browned--approximately 1 hour. Add diced dates in quantity desired and store in refrigerator.

title: boozed onion soup(serves 4)
directions: Cut onion in half through stem end, then into the thinnest slices possible.
Saute in a soup pot with a few tablespoons of butter.
When the onions are rich yellow, not brown, add the bourbon.
Wait a few seconds until the bourbon is hot, then set a match to the pot and let the booze blaze for 10 to 15 seconds.
To stop the blaze, cover the pot with a lid.
Add the chicken broth; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with cheese sprinkled on top once in a bowl.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add sour cream.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper. Drain.
Add tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Combine cheeses, egg and desired amount of parsley. Cook manicotti shells according to package directions until barely tender; drain. Stuff shells with cheese mixture.
Place filled shells in greased, shallow baking dish.
Pour meat/tomato sauce over shells. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown beef and onion in bacon drippings in Dutch oven.
Add next 7 ingredients; bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add potatoes, cover and simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: carrots cosmopolitan
directions: Scrape carrots; cut into diagonal slices, about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Stir together butter, juice, sugar, mustard and salt.
Pour over carrots.
Cook, covered, 30 to 40 minutes at 375° until carrots are tender.
If using microwave, cook carrots with small amount of water until almost done, add sauce and cook 2 or 3 more minutes.
Garnish with toasted almonds or pecans.
Serves 4.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: *Can substitute 6 medium potatoes, cooked and cubed.

title: 4 hour stew
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine all ingredients in a covered casserole dish.
Bake for 4 hours without peeking.

title: dill sauce haddock
directions: Mix ingredients and spread over fish of your choice.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: honey muffins
directions: Combine margarine and honey in a bowl; mix well.
Blend egg and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients; mix just until moistened. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Yields 16 muffins.

title: holiday pancakes
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 340° until bubbly.
Take out and add more cheese and paprika and bake 10 minutes more.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Mix all but cheese together and put in greased pan.
Lay the cheese over top of mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add prepared taco seasoning.
Mix and stir in picante and mushroom soup.
Spread refried beans in bottom of Pyrex (9 x 13-inch) dish.
Spread lightly with some picante and half the cheese.
Pour hamburger mixture over beans, jalapenos and sprinkle shredded cheese over top.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix together.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: apricot pineapple salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Cool completely and fold in cream cheese and whipped topping. Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix lemon juice, onion, spinach, sour cream and artichoke hearts and pour into 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oven fried lemon chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine yogurt, lemon juice, thyme, paprika, salt and pepper (to taste).
Cut chicken breasts in half and place in marinade; turn to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate approximately 15 minutes or overnight.
Remove from bowl; shake off excess.
Dredge breasts in bread crumbs; reserve on platter and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pecan rum cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; set aside. Mix butter and the sugars together and beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and mix well. Add pumpkin and vanilla and mix well. Gradually combine flour and pumpkin mixture, mixing well. Place pecans on bottom of greased 12-cup Bundt pan. Pour batter over nuts; bake in preheated 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes. Make holes in cake with long pick. Pour half of glaze over cake. Let stand 5 or 10 minutes. Invert over plate and repeat with remaining glaze. Cool.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Heat butter and milk in saucepan until butter is melted.
Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add hot milk and butter mixture; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in greased pan.

title: bahamian key lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until well blended.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Cover with whipped cream. Refrigerate a couple hours before serving.

title: easy stir-fry
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour over steak and set aside for 30 minutes or more.
Drain meat and drop into hot wok.
Cook until meat turns brown.
Remove from wok (with juice) and set aside.
Heat a small amount of oil in wok and stir-fry vegetables approximately 3 minutes.
Return meat and juice to pan and cook 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: easy baked turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Season turkey with margarine and salt. Place in a roasting pan with a good fitting lid.
Add 8 cups of hot water.
Place turkey in oven, making sure lid is on good.
After oven has again reached 500°, bake for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and do not open oven door until the next morning.
(I usually start mine at 8 p.m. and open oven door next morning at 6 a.m.)
This is very easy and the meat is very tender and moist.

title: texas peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add food coloring and peanuts.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butter and salt.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Remove from tins when cooled with a dull edged knife.
Makes 2 dozen 2-inch patties.

title: italian torta
directions: Prepare hot roll mix according to package directions.
While dough is rising, brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Add seasonings, water and tomato paste.
Squeeze excess moisture from spinach and combine with Ricotta cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and stir until combined. Fold in whipped topping and pecans.
Pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut salad into squares to serve.

title: david's meat loaf
directions: Combine.
Shape meat and place in pan to bake.
Cover shaped meat loaf with catsup, using a knife.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream together first three ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to batter.
Add chopped walnuts.
Form into balls and dip in sugar.
Put on cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of drinking glass.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes.

title: party pizza
directions: Fry ground chuck and onion, breaking into shreds with a fork. Sprinkle flour over the meat.
Mix in the pizza sauce, oregano, salt and pepper.
Spread on bread slices and top with cheese. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O with boiling water.
Add other ingredients and jell.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: In small saucepan, combine all ingredients except mushrooms. Bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms.
Simmer 5 to 6 minutes.
Place in bowl, cover and let stand overnight.
Stir occasionally.
Drain to serve.
Best if made 2 days ahead.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, unsalted; drain. Combine in saucepan the soup, cheese, egg, mayonnaise and milk.
Heat until cheese melts. Combine broccoli into soup mixture and pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle butter soaked bread bits over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Mix all together (use large bowl) well. Transfer to a 9 x 13 casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well. Add egg yolk and vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Divide dough in half. To half, add chocolate, mixing thoroughly.
Roll each half 1/8-inch thick on heavy waxed paper. Turn white part on chocolate dough.
Remove paper and roll up like you would a jelly roll. Wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly. Slice thin. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a 375° oven for about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice, cook broccoli, mix rice and broccoli with other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Chop green onions and mince until fine.
Combine with sour cream, mayonnaise and salts. Set overnight prior to serving.

title: dip
directions: Refrigerate for several hours.
Spread each one in layers. Serve with chips.

title: spinach splendor
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Brown hamburger with onion and garlic in a skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain.
Combine spinach, hamburger mixture and the next 6 ingredients in a glass casserole dish, mixing well.
Top with cheese and microwave on High for 6 minutes.

title: nancy's chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all other ingredients except water and beans; simmer over low heat (covered) 30 minutes.
Then add water and cook 1 1/2 hours longer.
Add beans, if desired, the last hour of cooking.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a shallow dish or heavy-duty Ziploc plastic bag.
Add tenderloin.
Cover dish or seal bag. Refrigerate 8 hours, turning often.
Remove tenderloin from marinade.
Cook, covered with grill lid, for 12 to 15 minutes or until thickest portion reaches 160°.
Cut into slices.

title: tacsos
directions: put the shells in the oven at 8 dorgres for 2 minits.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.

Brown in frying pan. Meanwhile, mix preserves, soy sauce, barbecue sauce and onion. Pour over browned chicken. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Ten minutes before time is finished, add the water chestnuts and green pepper.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain.
Mix tuna after draining. Mix peas after draining.
Stir.
Top with cheese and garnish with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, sugar, cinnamon, butter or vanilla in baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
Stir gently and bake 20 minutes longer until creamy thick.
Serve warm or cold with cream if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Put Ritz crackers (broken up) on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
A tossed salad completes meal.
A full meal in a snap.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Add flour mixture; blend.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix the drained tuna, clam chowder, sour cream, 3/4 of the Corn Flakes and rice.
Pour into lightly greased baking dish. Melt margarine and combine with the remaining 3/4 cup Corn Flakes. Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Measure the flour, sugar, oil, eggs, baking powder, orange juice and vanilla into large bowl of mixer and beat until well mixed.
Peel and slice apples.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Spread half the batter into pan.
Arrange half the apples on top.
Mix the cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle half on top of apples.
Add rest of batter, arrange rest of apples on top and sprinkle remainder of cinnamon and sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes, then remove from pan to rack.

title: tuna noodle salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Thaw broccoli in colander.
Once noodles are cooked, pour over broccoli in the colander.
Transfer broccoli and noodles to a large bowl.
Mix in tuna.
Add salad dressing to taste.
Grate carrot over top of salad and refrigerate.

title: hard clay
directions: Mix ingredients together in a big bowl.
Form into a big lump. Roll dough between 2 pieces of wax paper or plastic wrap with a rolling pin.
Use cookie cutters to cut out the shapes.
Punch a hole through each shape.
Let shapes dry for 1 week or dry them in a warm oven.
Paint and tie loops of yarn or string through holes.

title: party fruit punch
directions: Put bananas in blender. Add sugar. Add frozen orange mix, pineapple juice and ginger ale in a gallon jar. Add strawberries that have been cut in halves.

title: cool dairy delight salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add softened ice cream and then add the rest of the ingredients.
Place in an oiled 2-quart mold. Refrigerate until set.
Turn out on a bed of lettuce leaves to serve.

title: lazy day pickles
directions: Put in large container first 5 ingredients.
Put ice cubes on top and let stand 3 hours.
Drain and rinse well.
Put in large pan.
Boil next 4 ingredients for 5 minutes, then pour over pickles while hot.
Let cool.
Put in glass jars and store in refrigerator.
Keeps a long, long time.

title: cheese cake
directions: Coat a 9-inch round pan with the graham crackers.
Mix other ingredients and put in the pan.
Be sure to put pan of ingredients in another pan of hot water.
Leave 1 hour, then bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Take out and turn out carefully on a plate.
Decorate with fruit or nut topping or other as you wish.

title: mush
directions: Peel and boil carrots and potatoes together.
Drain.
Add milk and butter; whip until smooth.
Brown beef and onion.
Drain fat and then add gravy.
Put orange potatoes on plate and top with meat and gravy mixture.
Serve with cabbage and homemade bread or rolls.

title: tabbouleh(aperitif or salad from lebanon)
directions: Soak burghul until soft; in cold water it requires 1 hour, in warm water 1/2 hour.
Wash parsley and mint leaves thoroughly and chop very fine.
Chop onion very fine. Drain burghul. Add chopped parsley, mint and onion.
Mix well.
Add seasoning, chopped tomatoes, lemon juice and oil.
Mix well and serve. Serves 4.

title: chocolate-covered anything
directions: Melt the chocolate and shortening in a small bowl over simmering water or in the microwave.
Remove from heat, but keep over hot water while you're working.
Dip desired food into the chocolate, one at a time, lifting quickly from the mixture and tapping fork or tong lightly against the bowl to let excess chocolate drip off.
Place on a wire rack (to make cleanup easy, place a sheet of waxed paper underneath the rack.)
Store in a cool place or in the refrigerator.
Makes enough to dip 60 mini pretzels or 2 pounds of fruit.

title: chocolate crunch clusters
directions: Heat chocolate over hot water until partially melted.
Remove from hot water and stir rapidly until completely melted.
Then add nuts.
Cut marshmallows and cereal; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Yield: 2 dozen clusters.

title: skillet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a large iron skillet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Do not have to frost. Serve while warm with butter or with fresh fruit.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain.
Cook hamburger and onion together and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add chili powder to taste.
Cook low, about 30 minutes.

title: smothered tacos
directions: Cook hamburger; drain well.
Add taco seasoning; let simmer approximately 5 minutes.
Use 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Fill taco shells with meat, fold edges of shell and hold with toothpicks. Pour both cans tomato sauce over tacos.
Top with cheeses, green onions, black olives and jalapeno peppers (optional).
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Grate or chop frozen Butterfingers and add to mixture.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Add enough regular milk to fill freezer.
Freeze and enjoy!

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix well.
Drop by funnel in hot grease in an iron skillet. Serve hot with sprinkled powdered sugar.

title: special chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a casserole dish.
Put 2 slices of Swiss cheese over each breast.
Stir together the soup and the wine, and pour it over the chicken.
Sprinkle the stuffing mix over the top of the chicken.
Drizzle the melted butter over the top of everything and bake, uncovered, at 350° for an hour.

title: potluck potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets, then peel and cube.
Pour French dressing over warm potatoes, then refrigerate until cooled. Add remaining ingredients and gently mix.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: possum pie
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar and all chopped nuts to crushed crackers. Mix well and set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Add remaining 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla gradually and beat until peaks will hold.
Fold the 2 mixtures together carefully; turn into greased baking dish (or 9-inch pie plate).
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
When cool, top with whipped cream (and coconut, if desired) and chill.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix well all the ingredients to form into small balls.
Place balls on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar and blend well.
Combine flour, salt and soda; add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While cake is still hot, pour hot topping over it in the pan and let cool.
When completely cool, remove cake from pan.

title: cranberry conserve
directions: Ruby red and wonderful on hot biscuits.

title: orange baked flounder
directions: Combine the salt, pepper, orange juice, orange rind and oil. Place fish fillets in a lightly greased, shallow pan.
Pour sauce over fish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sunshine in a pocket
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Cook, uncovered, on High for 4 to 5 minutes, pushing egg to center of the dish after each minute.
Sprinkle cheese over eggs.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until melted, stirring once.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease 12-cup muffin tin.
In a large bowl, mix the dry ingredients.
In a smaller bowl, mix the egg, milk and butter. Make a depression in the center of the flour mixture and pour in the egg-milk mixture all at once.
Stir just until the dry ingredients are moistened and the batter is still lumpy.
Fold in the blueberries.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned about 25 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken.
While chicken is cooking, brown onion in oil in separate pan.
Add all ingredients to onion and simmer 30 minutes. Pour over chicken and cook in slow oven, 325°, for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: relish
directions: Put squash, onions and peppers in food processor.
After processing, put in a large bowl and cover with 1/4 cup Ball canning and pickling salt.
Cover with ice and let set for 1 hour, then drain.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Add squash, onions and peppers; cook for 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal while hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Butter a shallow dish that holds about 2 1/2 quarts and goes both into the oven and under the broiler.
Layer half the potatoes, sprinkling with salt and pepper.
Dot with butter. Layer half the onions, salt and pepper; dot with butter.
Repeat with remaining vegetables, ending with squash.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° until tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir together Parmesan and sour cream.
Spread on top of vegetables.
Broil on high for 3 to 5 minutes.
Watch carefully.
Top will be browned in spots.

title: grandma copple's caramel fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in heavy pan.
Heat to almost boiling stage and keep hot.
Dissolve 1 1/2 cups sugar in iron skillet; heat to golden brown.
Add pan mixture, one large spoon at a time, until all mixed.
(When adding to sugar, be careful and stir rapidly to keep from boiling over.)
Continue cooking to soft ball stage.

title: bread puff
directions: Use either an 8 x 10-inch pan or 1 round layer cake pan. Grease pan and sprinkle generously with brown sugar.
Mix in medium bowl: sugar, shortening, milk, flour and baking powder. Spread batter in pan over the brown sugar.
Dot the batter with margarine and sprinkle generously with brown sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: gob cake
directions: Mix all 6 minutes on high speed.
Pour into 2 greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let margarine and cheese stand at room temperature for about 2 hours.
Cream together thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix until smooth. Fill cookie press.
