Form straws on ungreased cookie sheet, using star plate.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: currant ginger shortbread
directions: Step 1: In the bowl of an electric mixer, cream the butter and sugar on medium speed, until smooth and light, about 3 - 4 minutes. Add the flour, salt, currants and ginger, mix the dough until well blended, about 3 minutes. Gather the dough into a ball and flatten slightly.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water until dissolved, then add pie filling and pineapple.
Put in refrigerator until jelled.

title: hoarhound candy
directions: Pour water over hoarhound.
Allow to stand 10 minutes. Strain.
Combine sugar, salt, syrup and water from hoarhound. Boil to soft crack stage.
Pour in thin sheet into well buttered baking sheet.
Mark into squares before candy hardens.

title: date cake
directions: Pour boiling water and soda over dates; let cool.
Add sugar, egg, shortening, vanilla and flour; add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 8 or 9-inch cake pan.
Serve with Dream Whip.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with foil.
Spray with nonstick spray. Cover foil with soda crackers.
Melt butter with sugar, stirring constantly.
Pour over crackers; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° until mixture is bubbly and crackers are floating (takes about 5 minutes).
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over all. Let sit until chocolate melts, then spread to cover.
Sprinkle with nuts.
When firm (not hard), cut into serving pieces.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Grease and flour a 9-inch round pan thoroughly.
Spread mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Frost, if desired; delicious without!

title: crabmeat munchies
directions: Cream butter.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well. Spread on split English muffins.
Broil until brown and bubbly. Cut into quarters.

title: grandma's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste (rinse cans with a little water), parsley flakes, basil, oregano, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil; turn down and simmer with lid on for 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Beat egg and add to cottage cheese.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Cook noodles.
Add vegetable oil and salt to water.
(This will keep noodles from breaking.) Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish with 2 to 3 tablespoons of hamburger mixture.
Place 3 noodles on top.
Then add 1/2 of hamburger mixture.
Put 1/2 of cottage cheese on top of hamburger. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: marinated coleslaw(lite choice)
directions: Combine cabbage, green pepper, onion and sugar substitute in a large bowl; stir well.
Combine Italian dressing, dry mustard and celery seed in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Pour dressing mixture over vegetable mixture, tossing gently to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or until thoroughly chilled.
Stir coleslaw lightly before serving and serve, using a slotted spoon.

title: cranberry-pineapple salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello powder and stir until dissolved. Add cranberries and pineapple.
Refrigerate until set.
Makes large salad - pretty too!

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding and everything else, then add chocolate and 6 ounces of chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Turn heat to 325° for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Place cream in double boiler, adding rice and salt. Cook until thick and creamy, about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Beat the eggs and sugar and fold into the rice, stirring all the while. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Place in serving bowl and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk; blend thoroughly.
Combine dry ingredients and blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in zucchini.
Spoon into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle chocolate bits and nuts over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb whole wheat coffee cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Blend, then mix dry ingredients. Stir well and add slowly to wet mixture.
Fold in rhubarb last. Pour into spring pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Best served warm.

title: angel pie
directions: Melt milk and marshmallows together over low heat, stirring constantly. Cool completely. Stir in 1/2 cup whipping cream until blended. Mix in 2 ounces grated chocolate.
Put into baked pie shell, top with 1/2 cup whipping cream (beaten until stiff) and 1 ounce grated chocolate.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Vanilla cracker, graham cracker or Oreo cookie crust in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: whole sirloin tip, roasted
directions: Salt and pepper sirloin tip.
Place meat into a low-sided baking pan.
No water.
Heat oven to 350° and bake 5 to 5 1/2 hours.
Take out and slice.
Skim grease off juice in pan and serve as is or you can thicken with flour.

title: peppermint chip ice cream
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir until well dissolved. Add half and half, vanilla and cream.
Add peppermint and coloring.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Freeze.
Remove dasher and stir in chocolate chips.

title: shrimp and fried rice
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan; add rice, stirring until rice is slightly browned.
Add shrimp, peas and carrots, mushrooms, salt, garlic powder and soy sauce.
Mix well.
Serve hot with additional soy sauce.
All ingredients may be cooked the day before and stored separately in the refrigerator until time to use.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh fruit with maple-vanilla yogurt dip(makes 8 servings)
directions: Combine the yogurt and maple syrup and chill. Core and slice the apple and pear. Sprinkle with lemon juice to prevent discoloration. Place the yogurt in a bowl in the center of a large platter and drizzle the yogurt with a few drops of extra maple syrup and sprinkle with the pistachio nuts. Arrange the apples, pears and grapes on the platter and serve. Preparation time: 10 minutes. Cooking time: 5 minutes.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil until clear.
Add eggplant and toss.
Add zucchini and peppers; cook 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Simmer, covered, 1/2 hour, and uncovered for 1/2 hour.

title: cream dried beef dip and rye bread
directions: Mix all together except the bread.
Take the middle out of one loaf of bread and put dip in the cavity.
Tear the other loaf of bread up into bite-size pieces to serve with the dip.

title: mom's best rice pudding ever
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Add all other ingredients and stir.
Cook over medium heat until hot, but not boiling.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart Pyrex mixing bowl and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Stir after 1/2 the baking time.
Serve warm or cold.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Fill paper cups in muffin pan 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar; beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 1 rounded teaspoon of cheese mixture into each cup of cake batter.
Bake as directed on cake package.
Makes 30 cupcakes.

title: herb baked potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and place in baking dish.
Top with margarine. Sprinkle on herbs.
Pour on the mushroom soup and top with slices of mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: seafood and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in nonstick skillet.
Add vegetables; stir-fry 4 minutes.
Add garlic; stir-fry 1 minute or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add shrimp and stir-fry sauce; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes until hot through.
Serve over rice.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir beef until light brown; drain.
Add onions and pepper; cook and stir until onions and pepper are tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Heat through.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Less time if you use 9 x 11-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: sliced sugar cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat shortening and butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed about 30 seconds or till softened.
Add about half of the flour to the shortening mixture. Then add the sugar, whole egg, milk, egg yolk, vanilla, baking soda and salt.
Beat till thoroughly combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Then beat or stir in the remaining flour.

title: bread machine roll mix
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. To prepare rolls, place water in bread machine pan. Add roll mix. Top with butter and yeast. Select dough setting. After 5 minutes, check mixture. Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of water or flour if needed. When cycle is complete, turn dough onto lightly floured surface. Punch down. Cover and let stand for 10 minutes. Divide into 12 portions. Shape each into a ball. Place on lightly greased pan. Cover and let rise for 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 1 dozen.

title: company eggs(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Remove crusts from white bread and place in buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan, covering bottom.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, mustard, ham, green pepper and mushrooms.
Pour over the bread.
Cover with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: curried broccoli stems
directions: Remove stems from broccoli and cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
(Store broccoli florets in refrigerator for another use.) Saute fresh ginger and garlic in oil until garlic begins to color. Add spices and cook for another minute.
Add broccoli stems and chicken stock.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until stems are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini sausage quiche
directions: Bake pie shell or make your own shell and place in pie dish. Make sure pie crust is cooled.
Cook the sausage until browned; remove sausage, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings.
Drain sausage and set aside.
Saute mushrooms; drain and set aside.
Melt butter in skillet and add zucchini and saute until tender; drain and set aside.
Place sausage in shell; sprinkle 1/2 cheese.
Spoon mushrooms on top of cheese; sprinkle remaining cheese.
Top with zucchini.
Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients, beating well. Pour into shell and bake for 55 minutes at 350° or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes one nine-inch quiche.

title: ruth's 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except 7-Up.
Beating slowly, add 3 cups flour (regular, not cake flour).
Fold in 6 ounces of 7-Up.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube cake pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Test cake with toothpick for doneness. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Combine next 5 ingredients and stir together.
Add orange juice mixture to flour mixture; stir until moist.
Do not beat.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts.
Put mixture into a greased pan and cook for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Yields 1 bread.

title: poutishum-wau
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until done.
Mash and put aside. Crumble ground meat into frypan.
Dice onion and fry 3 to 5 minutes until done. Drain grease and put hamburg and onion into baking pan or casserole dish.
Add creamed corn next.
Spread potatoes on top and butter on top.
Bake in oven at 350° until peaks start to brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and blend well.
Add broth and cook on medium, stirring occasionally until thick.
Add cream.
Stir in cooked spaghetti and chicken pieces until well coated.
Simmer for at least 5 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: ogeechee river goulash
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Remove from skillet.
Season beef with salt and pepper.
In same skillet, saute onions, celery and bell pepper until tender.
Add cooked beef, paprika and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Add tomatoes which have been pulverized with a blender or mashed with a fork.
Cook over low heat about 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve over rice.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add tomatoes, beans, soup and steak sauce.
Make paste of chili powder, flour, water and salt and heat over low heat with beef mixture, approximately 45 minutes until thickened and heated through.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and warm water together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Mix buttermilk and yeast with shortening mixture.
Put in oiled bowl and refrigerate.
When ready to use, roll out on floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased pan and let stand for 30 minutes or longer.
Bake at 400°.
May be kept in refrigerator in covered container for a week.
Makes 40 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: hamburger and brown gravy
directions: Roll hamburger and minced onion into meatballs.
Brown in oil and remove.
Put envelope of brown gravy and flour into oil until roux is right consistency.
Add beef consomme soup and water until gravy is thick enough.
Add meatballs and cook over low heat until done, about 30 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: scalloped corn (and oysters)
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Peel, being careful not to tear whites.
If yolk shows, discard.
Layer eggs, peppers, onion rings, carrots, 1 teaspoon spices and 1 or 2 bay leaves.
Repeat layers until reaching shoulder of gallon jar.
Add salt on top.
Heat vinegar and water to boiling; pour over eggs.
Let stand for 72 hours before using.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Beat eggs well and add water and salt.
Stir in flour with a spoon (dough is stiff so knead in the last of flour with hands like you would your bread dough).
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll each piece as thin as possible on a lightly floured cloth covered board.
Place between 2 towels until dough is partly dry.
Roll up as for a jelly roll.
With a sharp knife, cut into strips.
Shake strips loose, then they are ready to cook in chicken broth.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Beat eggs; add cake mix, pudding, cooking oil (or little less) and water.
Beat until well blended.
Grease pan with oil.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand a few minutes, then punch holes in cake.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: baked cheese balls
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients. Shape into 3\4 balls. Place about 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Bake until set, 15-18 min. Serve immediately. Yield about 6 dozen. 30 Callories per appetizer.

title: humdinger bread
directions: Spread on both sides of bread.
Fold bread together in tinfoil. Bake at 350° in hot oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: gob cake
directions: Mix altogether and beat well.
Pour into 2 cookie sheets (17 x 11 x 1-inch), greased and flour.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange supplement popsicles
directions: Mix orange supplement according to directions on packet.
Pour into Tupperware popsicle holders and freeze.
Freeze and enjoy. Tastes great.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn muffin mix; add in corn muffin mix.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: creamy chicken lasagna
directions: 1. Cook lasagna. Preheat oven to 350°. In saucepan cook butter, mushrooms, onion. Cook till tender. Add cream
cheese and bouillon. Cook till bouillon disolves.
2. Remove from heat and add sour cream, eggs, nutmeg, and
chicken. Mix all together well. In 13 x 9 baking dish,
layer half each of the lasagna noodles, chicken mixture
and cheese. Repeat layers. 3. Bake with cover on for 30 minutes,then 5 more minutes uncovered.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken in shallow baking dish.
Mix together Russian dressing, apricot preserves, onion soup mix and water.
Pour over chicken. Bake, covered in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Then add pineapple and bake uncovered for 30 minutes.
Serve over white rice if you like white rice.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple with juice.
Stir.
Add blueberry filling and stir well.
Pour into 9 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend together Crisco, sugar, salt and egg.
Add peanut butter.
Stir in flour sifted with soda.
Form the dough into balls the size of small walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press down with fork, then again at right angle to form a cross. Bake in moderately hot oven, 375°, for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix and baste as the ham balls bake.

title: pasta fagioli(pasta fazool)
directions: In a saucepan, cook garlic in oil until just browned.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Let cook 10 minutes.
Add beans and stir. Continue to simmer on low heat.
Cook macaroni until al dente. Drain and add to bean mixture.
Stir and add a little water, it tends to get too thick.
Add parsley and sprinkle with grated cheese and "Mangia!"

title: apple cake squares
directions: Mix apples and sugar together. Let set 15 minutes; keep stirred. After it has set 15 minutes, add the rest of the ingredients. Pour into greased square pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: laverne's shrimp gumbo
directions: Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and crab meat.
Serve over rice.
Serve with crackers.

title: maple glazed baby carrots
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan of salted boiling water.
Cook 6 to 10 minutes, until tender.
In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute for 2 minutes.
Remove garlic.
Add syrup.
Whisk to blend.
Drain and add carrots.
Add salt and pepper.
Over high heat, saute for 15 minutes or until carrots brown.
Dust with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana slush
directions: Mix well and freeze. Remove from refrigerator 2 hours before serving. When slightly thawed, mash with potato masher and add large bottle of 7-Up.

title: chocolate jimmy cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Mix in egg yolks, then add sifted flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix in flour and coffee slowly, alternating between the two.
Add chocolate jimmies.
Fold in nuts and egg whites.
Bake in an ungreased angel food tin for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water together.
Add blueberry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch dish and chill until firm or overnight.
Blend cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla flavoring together.
Spread over gelatin mixture and top with pecans (chopped).
Use as a salad or dessert.

title: supper popover
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir ground beef until brown; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, green pepper, 2 tablespoons flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Heat to boiling. Boil and stir one minute.
Pour into greased baking pan 13 x 9-inch.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: one dish macaroni beef
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart glass casserole.
Stir in onion.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Drain and stir in remaining ingredients; re-cover. Microwave on Defrost for 30 to 35 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and milk until soft ball forms in cold water (about 4 minutes).
Remove from heat and add butter and peanut butter.
Beat until it loses its gloss.
Pour into buttered pan and cut in squares.

title: bean hot dish
directions: Brown together beef, bacon and onion. Drain beans and add to beef mixture. Add the rest of the ingredients. Mix Well. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crawfish or shrimp casserole
directions: Cook onions,
peppers,	garlic and celery in oleo until tender.
Add
soups, parsley, green onions, shrimp and chopped pimento.
Heat
thoroughly;
stir
in
rice
and bread crumbs. Turn into a three quart casserole.	Sprinkle bread crumbs over casserole and bake at 350° for over 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of shrimp

title: swedish corn
directions: Beat egg a little with fork.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar and flour and add to egg.
Mix in corn.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons of sugar and dot with oleo.
Bake until solid at 375°.

title: pumpkin crunch cream pie
directions: Pour milk into mixing bowl.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk until blended; let stand 5 minutes.
Blend in pumpkin, spice, almonds, chips and 2 cups whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 4 hours or longer.

title: hot spiced wine mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Grease 9x13 or 9x15 cake pan with butter.
Spread 1 package of rolls in pan pressing seams together and cover bottom of pan. Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, 1 egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread over rolls.
Put second can of rolls on top.
Beat egg white slightly and spread on top of rolls.
Mix 1/2 c. sugar, nuts and cinnamon and sprinkle on top. Bake for 30-35 minutes at 325°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a pan.
Bring to a boil; boil for about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oats.
Stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper or aluminum foil.

title: diabetic jelly
directions: Combine and let stand 5 minutes.
Allow tapioca to soften. Bring mixture to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Skim off any foam, pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Can use any flavor as long as it is unsweetened.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Wash cabbage and boil in water until wilted; drain and separate leaves while cabbage is cooling.

title: tortilla black bean casserole
directions: In a large skillet combine onion, garlic, green pepper, undrained tomatoes, picante sauce and cumin.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer,
uncovered,
for
10	minutes.
Stir	in beans.
In a
x
x
2-inch
pan, spread 1/3 of the bean mixture over bottom.
Top with half of the tortillas, overlapping as	necessary.
Add
half of the cheese.
Add another 1/3 of mixture,
then
remaining tortillas and mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to
minutes
or	until heated through. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Let
stand	for
minutes. Top with tomatoes and green onions.	Serve with sour cream.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt oleo in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat; add Rice Krispies and stir until completely coated.
Using a buttered spatula (or fingers or wax paper), press evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: eggplant italiano
directions: Peel eggplant; slice
1/8-inch	thick.	Spread 2 tablespoons tomato sauce in
bottom
of
quart
casserole
dish. Layer 1/2 of eggplant, 1 can tomato sauce, 1/2 the oregano and 1/2 sharp cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover; microwave at High 14 to 16 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down lightly with a fork to make crisscross.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes.

title: honey surprise
directions: To honey, add the cinnamon stick, cloves and allspice.
Set container in a bowl of hot water for 20 minutes for flavors to develop.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine 1/2 cup cold milk with sugar, egg, vanilla and pudding and beat 1 minute or until thick.
Blend in 1/2 cup milk, flavorings and nutmeg.
Whip two minutes.
Blend in remaining milk.
Chill and serve.

title: taco dip(cold)
directions: Blend room temperature cream cheese, milk and Lipton onion soup mix together.
Spread on plate evenly.
Spread Ortega taco sauce over cream cheese.
Sprinkle lettuce, shredded cheese and desired topping over cream cheese.
Refrigerate for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Mix all of these ingredients together in a crock-pot.
Put on low for several hours.
Wonderful over raw vegetables or chips! Very hot!

title: new hampshire hash
directions: Fry peppers and onions in small amount of margarine until soft.
Add hamburger and cook until crumbly.
Add the tomatoes and rice, chili powder and salt and pepper.
Bake in a large casserole at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put into a baking dish and top with grated Jack cheese.
Bake 25 minutes in a moderate oven.

title: pound cake
directions: Put everything into a mixing bowl.
Do not sift.
Beat for 20 minutes at medium speed.
Scrape bowl occasionally.
Empty mixture into a well-greased Bundt or tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: star spangled trifle
directions: Cut the cake into 1-inch cubes and place in the bottom of a glass bowl.
Make up the gelatin according to directions.
Allow it to cool for a few minutes and pour it over the cake.
Place fruit over the cake.
Mix pudding according to directions and pour over fruit.
Refrigerate for at least 10 minutes.
Just before serving, top trifle with whipped cream, sweetened to taste, and garnish with fruit.
Enjoy!!

title: white nut loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Beat egg and milk together. Stir in well beaten egg and milk mixture.
Add nuts or fruits. Pour into greased bread loaf pan (8 x 4-inch).
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: hot dogs with hot peppers
directions: Cooks it, puts it in a bun with mustard, ketchup and hot peppers.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix in jar and refrigerate.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Layer the first three ingredients in large casserole dish (the casserole will "puff" when cooked).
Drizzle melted butter over the bread, cheese and scallops.
Beat milk, eggs, salt and mustard together.
Pour over mixture in casserole.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Blend the olive oil and vinegar.
Toss potatoes, beans and chicken with 2 tablespoons of the oil-vinegar dressing.
Toss the remaining ingredients and arrange onion rings on top.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix all ingredients and shape in balls.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 11 minutes.
Use a greased pan.
Be careful not to brown on bottom.
Makes 75 balls.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Stir together buttermilk, sugar, salt, pecans and butter in 6 cup dish.
Microwave on High 10 1/2 minutes, but stir every 3 minutes.
After 10 1/2 minutes, stir in baking soda until foamy. Cook on High for 1 minute.
(This last step gives pralines a caramel color.)

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix ingredients plus meat.
Place in pan and roast at 350° for 6 hours.
Remove beef and shred.
Return beef to sauce.
Serve on sandwich rolls.
This serves a big gang!

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Take medium sized cucumbers and lay in strong salt brine for three days, weigh them down with a plate or board so cucumbers are under brine.

Pour off the brine and lay in fresh water 2 days. Take weak vinegar and a piece of alum, put pickles in and let come just to a boil and then remove from stove and let them lay in the hot vinegar for 1 hour.
Remove pickles and cut in one inch chunks.

title: russian spiced tea
directions: Bring water to a boil with cinnamon and cloves.
Add tea; let steep.
Strain or remove tea bags.
Add fruit juices and sugar; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Will keep in refrigerator and freezes well.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello in boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water, strawberries, pineapple, sliced bananas and pecans.
Pour into a baking dish.
Chill until set.
Spread sour cream over salad.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk, salt and vanilla together and pour into a 9 x 11-inch buttered pan.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain fish; save juice.
Flake fish.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Pack firmly into greased glass loaf pan or casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until firm and brown.
Serves 5 or 6. Serve with cheese sauce and lemon wedge.

title: sweet and sour swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for 5 minutes.
Combine crumb mixture with meat, eggs and next four ingredients.
Shape into balls about an inch in diameter.
Heat shortening in skillet and brown meat balls.
Place meat balls in cooker pot.
Add grape jelly and barbecue sauce, dill weed and pepper.
Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: rick's shrimp and crab marsala
directions: Lightly saute garlic cloves and shrimp.
Then add jumbo lump crabmeat.
Add
parsley, basil, white wine and rosemary.
Pour mixture over pasta and sprinkle grated cheese to taste.
Yields 4 servings.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown and drain beef or sausage.
Mix the meat, egg, toast, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and garlic salt together.
Stuff meat mixture into cooked noodles. Place stuffed noodles into baking dish.
Mix tomato sauce, paste, 1 can of water (use paste can) and seasonings together; pour over noodles.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until cheese is completely melted.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening and cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix and chill.
Roll by teaspoonful into balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies until fine (this may be done in blender or by putting cookies in plastic bag and crushing by kitchen mallet); set aside.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Add oregano, garlic salt, tomato soup, water and vinegar and simmer for 30 minutes. In large baking pan, alternate layers of cooked noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut dry ingredients into shortening with a pastry blender. Drop egg into the water and beat. Add vinegar to egg mixture; blend into dry ingredients. Yields four 9-inch crusts.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread into even layer.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer. Spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Put butter evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook ground beef, bacon and onion in large skillet until meat loses color and onion is tender.
Drain only if there is an excessive amount of fat.
Stir in catsup, salt, mustard and vinegar.
Combine remaining ingredients in a 3-quart casserole. Stir in meat mixture.
Cover.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease 3-quart casserole dish and put in pineapple chunks which have been drained (save juice).
Combine sugar and flour and sprinkle over pineapple.
Sprinkle this with a little pineapple juice.
Put cheese on top and top with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: unreal brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Melt butter.
Put sugar in mixing bowl.
Mix about 3/4 of the melted butter in with the sugar.
In the remaining butter, over very low heat, add chocolate and melt.
Add melted chocolate to butter and sugar mixture.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in preheated oven. Do not overcook!
Brownies will be moist.

title: caramel roll ring
directions: Arrange frozen rolls in bundt pan.
Pour margarine over rolls.
Sprinkle brown sugar, dry pudding mix and nuts over margarine.

title: favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat in oil with onion and green pepper.
Drain off any grease (can use all Italian sausage if desired).
Add seasonings and cook briefly until it flavors the meat.
Add tomato sauce (adjust to own desired thickness, rinse cans with little water and add to sauce).
When heated through and boiling, add brown sugar to taste.
Adjust seasonings if necessary.
Cook on low for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve over spaghetti or use as sauce for lasagna.
Freezes well.

title: jellied ambrosia
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and place in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Add rest of ingredients and return to refrigerator to finish gelling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: In a small bowl combine mustard, pineapple juice and brown sugar; mix until sugar is dissolved.
Wrap each piece of chicken with bacon strip, fasten with toothpicks.
Brush mustard sauce over chicken and bacon.
Grill over hot coals, or broil in oven, for about 10 minutes, turning frequently and brushing with additional mustard sauce.
Remove wooden picks and serve.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. Serve with Fritos corn chips.

title: mini cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs together.
Put a vanilla wafer in bottom of a cupcake wrapper and place in muffin pan.
Fill cups 2/3 full and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 24 cakes.

title: bar-b-que sauce(for 4 to 6 servings ribs- double or triple for large groups.)
directions: Omit or lessen seasons to taste.

title: chili
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and garlic buds in butter until ground beef is no longer pink.
Add other ingredients.
Cook slowly for 2 hours or longer.
Cooked or canned red kidney beans may be added after chili is cooked.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Note:
Mix in top of double boiler.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown sirloin strips with onions, green pepper, mushrooms, water, butter and tomatoes.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: quick and tasty jambalaya
directions: In a large skillet, saute rice mix as package directs.
Stir in 2 cups water, chicken, sausage, onion, tomatoes with juice from can, garlic, hot pepper suace and contents of seasoning packet. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Stir in shrimp and green pepper.
Simmer for 10 more minutes until most of the liquid is absorbed.
More pepper sauce can be added if not hot enough.
Serves 5.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Sift sugar, nutmeg and flour in a bowl.
Add beaten eggs; stir well.
Place rhubarb in a dish.
Pour mixture over rhubarb; mix well.
Place in a 9-inch prepared pie crust; dot with butter. Lattice top pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower oven to 350° and bake for an additional 30 minutes.

title: chocolate nut cake
directions: Fix oatmeal mixture; let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in butter and sugar; add egg and mix well.
Add flour mixture.
Fold in half of chips and spread in greased and floured pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Sprinkle remaining chocolate and nuts on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° about 45 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serve with Cool Whip (optional).

title: miss piggy's precious pink punch
directions: Chill the beverages.
Pour into bowl; add fruit and mint. Stir with spoon; serve to football fans.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: In bowl with fork, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Slowly stir in pineapple, pecans, green pepper and onion salt.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in rest of nuts.
Wrap in foil.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: To slightly beaten eggs, add sugar and beat.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add flour alternately with hot milk. Add vanilla.
Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° until done.

title: butter pecan rolls
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Place 24 frozen rolls around inside of pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding over rolls.
Melt butter, brown sugar and cinnamon. Stir until smooth.
Add chopped pecans and pour over rolls. Spray a piece of foil and cover Bundt pan. Refrigerate overnight or on counter for several hours.
Remove foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from the oven and cool for 5 minutes only.
Loosen edges.
Place large plate over pan, invert and allow ring of rolls to fall from pan onto the plate.
Slice or break apart to eat.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Whip butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour gradually.
Add whipping cream.
Mix well.
Add flavorings. Mix well.
Pour mixture into greased and floured Bundt pan or cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes to 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Let cool for 30 minutes.
Wrap in aluminum foil and store in refrigerator 1 day before cutting, if you can.

title: snicker bars(low calorie)
directions: Chop Grape-Nuts fine in food processor.
Allow ice milk to soften.
In 8 x 8-inch pan, press mixture into pan.
Freeze for 20 minutes; remove from pan.
Cut into 8 portions.

title: coconut pies
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and butter, mixing well.
Add buttermilk and canned coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine in order as written.
Beat egg white to a soft peak. Fold in egg white.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: polish meatball-sour soup
directions: Mix ground veal, egg, salt and pepper to taste and seasoned bread crumbs thoroughly.
Form into walnut size balls.
Broil to brown.
Drain fat and set aside.
Into 4 or 5 quarts of boiling water, add onion, garlic, celery, carrots, parsley, beef bouillon cubes or canned broth, bay leaf, salt and pepper, potatoes and wax beans.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add meatballs and simmer 45 minutes.

title: mountain pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and salt.
Add the cup of whipping cream; do not whip it.
Stir well and let set while you prepare the crust.
(It helps the brown sugar granules to dissolve.) Prepare the crust and put into a pie plate.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt margarine, remove from heat.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add melted margarine to flour mixture.
Combine last three items and add to mixture.
Stir well. Pour into unbaked (9-inch) pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine oats and boiling water, stirring well.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream butter.
Add sugars and beat well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, vanilla and oatmeal mixture, beating until blended.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Layer vegetables in order given in 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon just before serving and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: mamaw's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients well, then add raw apples chopped very fine. Mix well.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake in 375° oven about 45 minutes. This makes a very large cake.

title: potato cakes
directions: Shape cold mashed potato in small cakes.
Roll in flour. Butter hot omelet pan and put in cakes.
Brown one side, turn and brown the other side.
Add butter as needed to prevent burning.

title: greek sauce
directions: Saute meat, onions and garlic until meat no longer is pink. Drain off any fat.
Add rest of ingredients, let simmer until a nice consistency and all spices are blended.
Great to serve on hot dogs and hamburgers, or if brave, alone!

title: cheesy macaroni-mushroom bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Rinse macaroni and set aside.

title: company's coming bloody mary mix
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients in a 1 1/2-gallon pitcher.
Mix well. Serve with or without vodka. Garnish with a sprig of celery.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice in 3 cups of water for 45 minutes or until done. Heat milks in pan, but do not boil.
Beat in a bowl the 4 yolks, 3/4 cup of sugar and vanilla.
Add the boiled rice to the milk and stir.
Add egg yolk mixture and simmer 15 minutes until slightly thickened.
During the last 5 minutes, add raisins, if desired. Put in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.

title: ugly thing
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter or oleo and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 3 eggs together and pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden.

title: macaroni in cheese sauce
directions: Beat eggs and add oil, flour and salt.
Heat in large pan, add milk and stir constantly, cooking over medium heat until sauce starts to boil.
Lower heat and cook until thickened (about 3 minutes).
Add mustard and grated cheese.
When cheese melts, stir in macaroni.
Place in 350° oven and bake 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and cocoa. Add water and milk; boil 1 minute until thick. Add margarine and vanilla. Serve warm.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a buttered casserole.
Can be topped with the following topping.

title: banana bread
directions: *To sour milk, add 1/4 teaspoon of vinegar and let set 3 to 4 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the ingredients in the order listed, into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Over this, pour 1 white cake mix, mixed according to package directions.
Bake 1 hour.
May be served warm or cold.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Coat an 8-inch square pan with cooking spray.
Put peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter in a 3-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes until butter melts and chocolate chips look soft and glossy, but still retain their shape.
Stir until smooth, then stir in marshmallows. Microwave on High 45 to 60 seconds.
Marshmallows will be slightly melted.
Stir to mix, then stir in cereal until well blended. Spread into pan.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours until firm.
Contains 175 calories, 0 cholesterol and 11 g. fat.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: steak on a stick
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Marinate beef overnight in refrigerator.
Drain and grill.
Use sauce to baste while cooking. Soak wooden skewers several hours in water before use to prevent burning over the fire.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Rinse with cold water.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve warm or cold.

title: white chocolate cranberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil so foil extends 2 inches on the long sides.
Lightly butter bottom and sides of pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
In another bowl, mix at medium speed, butter and sugars together for 2 minutes, until creamy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each one.
Beat in vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture until just combined.
Using a wooden spoon, stir in white chocolate, cranberries and nuts.
Scrape batter into pan. Smooth out.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes on middle rack until top is golden brown and toothpick inserted 2 inches from center has a few moist crumbs clinging to it.
Cool bars.
Lift out of pan using foil as handles, invert and peel off foil.
Invert again and cut into bars.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, removing hard stems.
Cook Minute rice according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat loaf ingredients and form into loaf. Place in loaf pan.

title: easy scallop potatoes
directions: Scald milk with butter.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Put in a buttered, 2-quart casserole.
Mix the potatoes with dry cornstarch.
Pour scalded milk over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
I never add salt.
It curdles the milk.
The butter helps to season.

title: easy no bake candy cookies
directions: Melt margarine in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in sugar, salt, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil exactly 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, then oats.
Mix thoroughly and drop onto wax paper.
Cool, then chill.
Store airtight.
If candy cookies stick to paper, peel them off gently. Yields about 56.

title: super homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, whites separate, then yolks.
Mix half and half, Milnot, junket and eggs.
Add milk, then sugar and vanilla.
This recipe works for any flavor by adding fruits, nuts, etc.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender.
Mash and mix with milk and sugar; run through a coarse strainer.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes in 425° oven. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes or until set.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Over shortening, sugar and salt pour boiling water.
Blend and cool.
Add beaten eggs.
Sprinkle yeast into the lukewarm water and stir until dissolved.
Combine with egg mixture.
Add flour. Blend well.
Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.

title: liptauer
directions: Soak minced onion in 1 tablespoon water for 10 minutes.
In a cup combine dry mustard with 2 teaspoons warm water and let stand 10 minutes.
Combine butter and cream cheese, blending well.
Add onion, dry mustard, anchovy fillets, capers, caraway seed and white pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack into a 2-cup mold.
Chill until firm.

title: snack time dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vegetable dippers. Mix well and chill. Serve with vegetable dippers. Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: tuna cheese ball
directions: Put all ingredients together; stir to make a flat ball, then put in serving dish; chill a few hours.
Serve with crackers.
When ready to serve, pour cocktail sauce over top.
This is great.

title: coffee slush - 2
directions: Mix all together and freeze. Keep in the freezer until ready to serve.

title: crawfish fettuccine
directions: Melt butter; cook onions and garlic until transparent.
Add salt, peppers and crawfish.
In a separate pot, melt cheese and soup.
Add crawfish and onions to cheese mixture.
Add dash of Worcestershire sauce and a dash of crab boil.
Mix in cooked fettuccine.
Add milk if mixture is too thick.

title: fruited pork chops
directions: Place chops in baking dish; cover liberally with soy sauce. (Do not salt chops, soy is salty enough.)
Cover with foil and cook 35 to 40 minutes in a 325° oven.
Uncover and turn chops, adding more soy sauce, if desired.
Place on each chop 1 slice of pineapple, 1 round of green bell pepper and top with prune. Continue to cook until done.
Additional pineapple, prunes and peppers may be added.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Combine water and bouillon cubes in potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer 12 minutes.
Melt butter. Blend flour and cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Cook over low heat; do not boil.

title: white christmas meringues
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add sugar, a tablespoon at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Fold in vanilla, nuts and chips.
Drop by tablespoon onto a cookie sheet lined with foil.
Do not peak.
Place cookies in a preheated 400° oven.
Turn off immediately.
Leave overnight or at least 6 hours.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add brown and white sugar; mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add potato chips and nuts.
Mix all together.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.
Store in tight can.

title: catfish gumbo
directions: Cut fillets into bite size pieces.
Cook celery, onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Add bouillon, tomatoes, okra and seasoning; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add catfish.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes longer, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Remove bay leaf. Place 1/3 cup rice in each of 6 bowls.
Fill with gumbo.

title: cheesecake dream cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Stir in melted butter. Reserve 1/3 cup crumbs.
Press into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Put cereal in large bowl and pour boiling water over it.
When it cools a little, add buttermilk and baking soda; stir well. Cream together sugars, eggs, oil and molasses.
Add to cereal mixture and mix well.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Do not stir again; just spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix butter, water and chicken broth in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pur over rice and noodles in a 1 1/2-quart Corning dish. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until sugar dissolves.
Boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over Rice Krispies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into bars.

title: bow tie pasta salad
directions: Combine ingredients in food processor and chop.
Pour mixture over bow tie pasta.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.

title: blue cheese potato salad
directions: While potatoes are warm, drizzle with a little vinegar. Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, mustard and salt.
Pour over potatoes.
Add the onion, celery, green pepper and eggs.
Mix carefully!
Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Fold in Blue cheese just before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach dip
directions: Take insides out of pumpernickel; save for dip.
Mix all ingredients together and fill inside of pumpernickel.

title: macaroons
directions: Beat
egg
whites.
When fluffy, add sugar and vanilla. Add coconut
and corn flakes.
Drop on greased pan with spoon. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: aunt vera's beef goulash
directions: Saute onion in a small saucepan until onion is almost transparent.
Add stewing meat and brown.
Add seasoning, salt, pepper, celery powder, garlic powder and parsley to taste.
Add water, enough to cover ingredients.
Cover and simmer for two hours.
Add carrots and cook until done.
Just before serving, add the two packets of instant gravy.
Mix well and serve.
It is very good served over noodles.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: In bowl blend ingredients, except crescent rolls.
Separate the rolls.
Split 1/4 cup pepperoni mixture on each roll.
Place cut side seam down on cookie sheet.
Start at short side and roll up.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: margie's squash casserole
directions: Mix milk, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Add to squash and mix well.
Add cracker crumbs to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Save small amount of cheese for topping.

title: stuffed cookies
directions: Sift flour; measure to resift 3 times with baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and butter; blend in sugar gradually.
Add eggs; beat until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately in 2 or 3 portions, beginning and ending with flour and beating well after each addition.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll on lightly floured board to about 1/8-inch thickness; cut out with any desired cookie cutter about 2 inches in diameter.

title: tomato basil soup
directions: In large pan melt butter, add onions and cook until caramelized; stir while cooking.
Add other ingredients simmer 5 minutes.
Put in individual serving bowls and garnish with fresh basil.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix together and bake.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Use 2 teaspoons for a cup of hot water.

title: golden velvet carrots
directions: Melt margarine in top of double boiler over boiling water. Pour margarine into blender container.
Add 1/2 cup carrots, all of juice, vanilla and cinnamon; process at medium speed until smooth.
Return margarine mixture to double boiler; add remaining carrots.
Heat and garnish.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: blushing peach delight
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle unflavored gelatine over water; let stand 1 minute.
Add hot juice and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Stir in reserved syrup.
Chill, stirring occasionally until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in peaches and grapes.
Turn into 5 1/2-cups mold and chill until firm.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Put the pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour dry cake mix over top of filling; spread.
Cut butter in pats and place all over top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Make sure to check it after 30 minutes.
Can add Cool Whip on top or you can use vanilla ice cream.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour loaf or tube pan. Dump all ingredients in large bowl. Mix together. Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 40 - 50 minutes.

title: hunan beef with peppers
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly combine brown sugar, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Add beef; turn to coat.
In large skillet, heat oil and cook garlic, pepper and beef mixture over high heat, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes or until beef is browned.
Stir in red and green peppers and green onions; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add salt and pepper.

title: orange and cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix jello (dry) in cottage cheese, then add drained oranges. Whip Dream Whip and add to the other ingredients.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Slit peppers and remove seeds.
Stuff small amount of cheese into pepper halves.
Mix remaining cheese with sausage.
Knead mixture.
Gradually add biscuit mix and continue kneading to make dough.
Pat out small amount of dough and shape around stuffed pepper half to form egg shape.
Roll in Shake 'n Bake, in beaten eggs, then in Shake 'n Bake again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue rice
directions: Saute onions, celery, green peppers and mushrooms until soft. Throw the still-moist rice into the saute mixture and brown until golden.
Prepare a sauce using bottled barbecue sauce, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce.
(These measurements can be played with according to individual taste!) Pour over rice mixture and mix until heated.
Serve!

title: kamabuko tempura
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use a teaspoon to drop the mixture into heated cooking oil.
Deep fry; drain on paper towels.

title: dressed up squash
directions: Cook squash, onion and carrots in salted water for 10 minutes. Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in vegetables.
Mix well.
Melt butter and add stuffing mix.
Spread 1/2 of crumbs in bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Spoon vegetables on top. Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hobo supper
directions: Place a large patty of seasoned ground beef on a square of aluminum foil.
On meat, place 4-6 slices of onion, 4-6 slices of potatoes, and 4-6 strips of carrots.
Pull the foil up to form a cup and over each ground beef patty pour 1 tablespoon of the sauce (see sauce recipe listed below).
Twist the foil edges tightly. Place on cookie sheet and bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves any number desired.

title: easy party rolls
directions: Slice entire package rolls horizontally.
Place ham on bottom and top with cheese.
Replace top of rolls.
Melt butter and add remaining ingredients and stir.
Roll over rolls.
Refrigerate overnight or freeze for later.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: pigs in the blanket
directions: Blend (crumble) first 5 ingredients.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Chill.
Roll out and cut in 3-inch squares.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 40 to 45 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts and chill.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix the pineapple juice and lemonade together.
Add the sherbet.
Pour Ginger Ale over mixture and serve.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, chocolate, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: valerie's lo-cal jello fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows in boiling water using mixer or blender.
Add yogurt and mix until smooth.
Add cold water to reserved juice to make 1/2 cup.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in pineapple.
Put in mold; chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: bachelor buttons
directions: Measure and sift together flour, salt and soda.
In a separate bowl, cream sugar and shortening; add egg, beating until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and nuts or fruit and stir with rubber spatula to blend; add flour mixture.
Drop from a teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet or shape into crescents with floured fingertips.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes.

title: pease porridge hot
directions: Cook bacon in large saucepan until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain on absorbent paper and crumble.
Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings. Cook and stir onions in reserved drippings until tender and lightly browned.
Add soup, then gradually mix in water.
Bring to a full boil.
Add rice, salt and bacon.
Cover; remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: turkey bake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well. Spread in greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Let stand a few minutes to set. Cut into squares and serve with gravy.

title: cranberry pear relish
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, place pears and syrup, wine, cinnamon stick and cloves.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 10 minutes. Remove pears, cinnamon and cloves.
Reserve 6 pear halves and dice remainder.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over broccoli.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Beat butter and shortening for 30 seconds.
Add the sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture until well combined.
Cover and chill for 3 hours.
Working with half the dough at a time, on a lightly floured surface, roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until done.
Makes 36.

title: vanilla-butter sugar cookies
directions: In bowl, combine sugar and butter; beat until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture until completely blended.
Chill for 30 minutes.
On a lightly floured surface roll dough to a 1/4 inch thickness.
Cutters should be dipped in flour.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a very moist and chewy cookie.

title: open house punch
directions: Mix all in punch bowl, except 7-Up.
Add this just before serving.
Make ice float by freezing some of the fruit juice and citrus slices.
A few drops of red food coloring will give this punch a festive color, but this is optional.
Serves 25.

title: oven brisket
directions: Marinate brisket in liquid smoke overnight.
Mix Worcestershire sauce with barbecue sauce.
Drain liquid smoke from brisket and pour sauce mix over brisket in roaster.
Cover brisket with onion slices and bake at 350°, covered, 4 to 6 hours.

title: taco pie
directions: Spread bean dip on pizza pan or glass tray.
Mash avocado and lemon juice together and spread over dip layer.
Mix sour cream, taco seasoning, and taco sauce together and spread over avocado mix.
Dice tomato and sprinkle on; chop spring onion and sprinkle on; shred Cheddar cheese and sprinkle on.
Use black olives for garnish if desired.

title: strawberry daiquiri mix
directions: Mix all ingredients. Freeze. Let thaw 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell until brown.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Sift flour, salt and pepper together.
Dip pork chops in mixture and shake off excess. Heat oil in large skillet and cook chops over medium-high heat until done. Remove from skillet.

title: mess cake
directions: Take angel food cake and break into bite-size pieces.
Place in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Spread vanilla pudding over half of pan and chocolate over the other half.
Place cherry pie filling in middle covering some of each flavors of pudding.
Spread Cool Whip over entire pan and chill.

title: oven fried rice
directions: Combine in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in a large saucepan.
Combine Velveeta, beans, corn, Ro-Tel and tomatoes; add hamburger and onions.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake and mix in quart jar.

title: old favorite pancakes
directions: Heat oil in pan on medium to medium-high.
Pour mix in pan and brown on both sides.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip
chicken
in melted butter and then roll in crushed Rice Krispies.
Bake
at
325° for 45 to 50 minutes, depending on how much and how many pieces of chicken.
Do not cover.

title: layer lettuce salad
directions: Break one head lettuce in decorative glass bowl.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup celery, 1/2 cup green pepper, one thin sliced onion (or 1/2 cup chopped green onion) and one box frozen peas, uncooked.
Spread with 2 cups real mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with one tablespoon sugar.
Add enough bacon bits for a light covering and sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cover.
Make a day ahead and refrigerate.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients on a shallow dish or plate and serve with nacho chips.

title: cream corn casserole
directions: Combine corn bread mix, cream corn, kernel corn, sour cream, eggs and melted margarine;
mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 35-40 minutes.
Serves 4-6.

title: corn bread
directions: *Add 1 teaspoon vinegar to make the sour milk.

title: savory pork chops
directions: Brown chops with garlic on medium-high both sides; place on platter and set aside. Combine in a bowl the next 5 ingredients. Put the chops back in the pan and pour the mixture over the chops. Cover and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes. Add water if needed. Turn the chops only once. Remove chops when done.

title: almost better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is hot, poke 12 to 15 holes with handle of wooden spoon in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake, then caramel and butterscotch sauce over this.
Cool cake in refrigerator.
Before serving, spread Cool Whip over cake; sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cut up large shrimp. Fry bacon until crisp. Add shrimp, onion, green pepper and garlic; cook until tender. Add flour and seasonings. Add tomatoes and cook until thick. Serve over rice.

title: it's-a-snap cheesecake
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatine over 1/4 cup cold water. Let stand 1 minute. Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry the ground beef and onion in a large skillet and season to taste.
Add the soup and water to the beef.

Add the cheese. When the cheese is melted, mix well and pour over the dry egg noodles which are in a buttered casserole dish. Mix these up after pouring on the soup, meat mixture and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: kifle(bubba's small nut rolls)
directions: Put flour in large mixing bowl; crumble in compressed yeast. Cut in margarine with pastry blender until crumbly.
Add egg yolks and sour cream.
Mix well (use hands).
Form into a ball; knead on lightly floured surface until smooth (5 to 10 minutes). Divide dough into 3 equal parts.
Wrap in wax paper and chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour.

title: grandma d's bread(5 loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add rest of ingredients. Knead.
Put in greased bowl.
Let rise until double; punch down and rise again.
Shape into 5 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add sweet potatoes, then butter; add cinnamon, allspice and eggs all together and then add vanilla flavor.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice squash in 1/2-inch pieces.
Boil for 3 minutes or until tender.
Drain, then add onions, eggs and seasonings.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 1-quart buttered casserole dish.
Mix butter and crumbs and sprinkle over squash. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until browned.

title: sports sunday sandwich
directions: Halve the bread horizontally.

In a large bowl combine the olives, onion, lettuce and bell pepper and toss with dressing. Spread half of the salad mixture on the bottom half of the bread. Top with single layers of half of the meats, cheese and tomatoes. Top with the remaining salad and repeat layers of meats, cheese and tomatoes.
Cover with the top of the bread and press down. Cut like pie to serve.
Serves 8.

title: oven stew
directions: Layer in order.
Sprinkle tapioca over all.
Add tomato juice. Cover tightly and bake for 4 hours at 250°.
Do not open lid until finished baking.

title: chocolate chip dessert
directions: Dip cookies in milk and layer in dish.
Put Cool Whip on next layer.
Continue layers and end with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Mix each package of Jell-O with boiling water and cold water in separate pans. Chill overnight. Mix pineapple juice with sugar. Heat until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat. Add lemon Jell-O to hot juice. Add 1/2 cup cold water. Chill 1 hour and 15 minutes. Meanwhile, cut 3 flavors of Jell-O into cubes with a sharp knife. With a mixer, cream together cream cheese and milk until smooth. Add lemon Jell-O and juice to cream cheese and beat until well mixed. Fold in cubed Jell-O. Refrigerate and chill overnight.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Place marshmallows in pan and stir until melted.
Take off heat and stir in Rice Krispies.
Pour in pan and press down until even in pan.
Cool and cut in 2-inch pieces.

title: cheddar potato casserole
directions: Prepare the mashed potatoes or bring leftover potatoes to room temperature.
Season to taste.
Beat egg yolks into mashed potatoes until well mixed.
Stir in the cheese, onion, green pepper, and celery salt.
Salt to taste.
Whip egg whites into soft peaks and fold into the potato mixture.
Spoon into well buttered casserole, about 1 1/2-quart size.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley sprig.
Serve immediately.

title: spoon tacos
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add chili and taco sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Layer corn chips, hamburger mixture, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese in a 13 x 9-inch greased casserole dish. Heat, uncovered, in a 400° oven until cheese melts.

title: chili sauce for hot dogs
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Combine all the ingredients and add to meat. Simmer 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon; cut in shortening and butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add potato and milk; stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface; knead 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to one-half inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter. Place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with melted butter.

title: festive broccoli
directions: In heavy skillet with cover, melt butter; add remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until crisply tender, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey a la king
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour well.
Add broth and milk all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thick and bubbly. Add meat, mushrooms and peas.
Heat through.
Serve over toast or waffles.

title: wassail punch
directions: Pour water over tea bags and steep for 4 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
In very large pan, combine tea, apple cider, orange juice, cranberry juice and sugar.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Yields 2 gallons.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt oleo and add ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: brown rice(microwave)
directions: Mix ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish. Dot with butter. Cover and microwave on High 18 minutes.

title: old-fashioned rich white cake(3 layers)
directions: Sift and mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Blend Crisco, milk and vanilla into mixture.
Add egg whites.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Make 3 wells.
In the first well, put the salad oil.
In the second, put the vinegar. In the third, put the vanilla.
Pour water over all ingredients and mix on low speed.
Pour batter into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together.
Gently pack into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour or until loaf shrinks from sides of pan.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls and then into granulated sugar.
Bake.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks and then nuts and pineapple.
Beat egg whites; then mix all together.
Line a 10 x 8 x 2-inch pan with crushed graham crackers.
Spread mixture; bake in a 350° oven.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch pan in layers:
lettuce, chopped celery and green onion.
Sprinkle frozen peas over top.
Spread with mayonnaise.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: country tea cakes
directions: Cream butter.
Add eggs, salt, milk, baking powder and vanilla.
Work in the flour to form a roll. Flour board and roll to form a thin layer.
Cut the desired size and bake on cookie sheet until light brown.

title: mary ann's fettucine zucchini
directions: Melt margarine with olive oil in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; saute for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini and saute 10 minutes.
Add herbs and spices; saute until zucchini is almost tender, then add lemon juice and tomatoes.
Simmer. Cook fettucine in salted boiling water until al dente and drain. Toss with zucchini mixture and top with Parmesan cheese.
Serve at once.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares or designs with cookie cutter.
Serve.

title: black-eyed pea supper dish
directions: Cook sausage in large frying pan and drain.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring vegetables into sausage.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Pour in beans with liquid in can.
Cover and simmer slowly for at least 15 minutes.
Serve very hot with grated cheese sprinkled on top.
(This dish is best when it can be prepared ahead of time.
The flavors blend better.)

title: "rice and beans" meal
directions: Combine 1 quart of cold water and kidney beans in 2-quart saucepan on high heat.
When it comes to a boil, add olive oil, garlic, salt, pepper and 1 whole onion and turn down to simmer. Cook approximately 1 hour.
In a large skillet, put enough oil to saute 1 medium onion, sliced or diced.
Add rice, salt, pepper and 1 cup of cold water.
Cover and steam for about 30 minutes, adding rest of water midway, until rice is cooked.
Serve rice and beans separately.
Great with Italian bread!

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix oil, dill seed and dressing mix; pour over crackers.
Mix gently.
Place in airtight container.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine ingredients in large boiler or slow cooker and heat at low temperature for about 3 hours.
Serve hot.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: sam's salsa supreme
directions: Brown hamburger, garlic, onion and mushrooms.
Drain grease and add Sam's salsa.
Remove from heat.
In casserole dish, layer ingredients as follows:
salsa mixture, lettuce, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, tomatoes, Mozzarella cheese and olives.
Bake in oven at 325° until cheese melts, about 15 minutes.
Eat with Sam's tortilla chips.
Great for a party.

title: oreo cookie freak out
directions: Crush 2 rolls of cookies and combine with melted butter. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice ice cream and lay on top of cookies.
Heat fudge sauce, just until spreadable consistency, and spread over ice cream.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over fudge sauce. Spread whipped topping over all.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine eggs, potatoes and onion.
Combine oil, vinegar and salt.
Pour over potatoes and chill for 2 hours or overnight.
Add mayonnaise before serving.

title: marshmallow fudge sauce
directions: Combine chocolate marshmallows and milk in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave at High setting 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is melted and marshmallows are soft.
Stir until marshmallows melt and mixture is blended.
Serve warm over ice cream or cake.
Makes 1 cup.
May be stored in refrigerator.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Blend with a mixer the Eagle Brand, Cool Whip and pink lemonade.
Add lemon juice.
Taste.
Add more lemon juice to suit your taste.
Cover pies.
Freeze or refrigerate approximately 1 hour.

title: glazed apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar, nectar and oil in a large mixing bowl. Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until it springs up when touched.

title: creamy chicken-broccoli noodles
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, prepare noodles according to package directions.
Add seasoning packets; drain off most of liquid. Stir in mushroom soup, milk and cheese.
Add chicken and broccoli. Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients
together.	Serve as a dressing for salad or as a dip for fried vegetables or chicken drumetts.

title: spiced fruit
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar and spices together.
Pour this hot over fruit 3 times.
The third time, boil the juice to a syrup.
Then heat your fruit with the syrup and can.

title: best ever pineapple cake
directions: Beat with mixer until smooth.
Spread on cake while it is still hot.
Cool in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: aunt ada's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; blend in melted butter, flour, vanilla, salt, sugar and syrup.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Now gently pour syrup mixture over pecans and bake in hot oven at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake 40 minutes longer.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Put milk in bowl.
Pour in lemon juice and stir.
Pour in pineapple and nuts; mix well.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate about 3 hours.

title: fiesta cheesecake
directions: Mix tortilla chips and melted butter and press into 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: good biscuits
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients together.
Sprinkle Bisquick mix on cutting board.
Cut out.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 18 minutes.

title: quick picante sauce
directions: Place tomatoes in blender.
Pulse on several times to achieve desired chunkiness.
Place in sealable jar and stir in chopped jalapeno, dehydrated onion and salt.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Will keep for 2 weeks or so in refrigerator.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash potato.
Add confectioners sugar to potato to make a stiff
dough.
Roll
out
on waxed paper dusted with confectioners sugar (like a pie crust).
If too much for one, divide and	make 2.	Spread peanut butter over entire surface.
Roll up
like
a jelly roll.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice.
Keep refrigerated. Leftover mashed potatoes may be used.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put the ingredients in a microwave safe bowl in order listed (don't stir).
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
After cooking, stir in 1/2 cup chopped nuts (any type).
Pour fudge in a butter pan and refrigerate for about an hour before cutting.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and Crisco until crumbly.
Add egg and milk all at once and stir with fork until mixed.
Makes enough for 1 double crust pie shell.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak diagonally across grain into very thin slices.
Cut into strips about 2 inches long.
Set aside.
In large skillet, melt butter; add garlic.
Cook over medium heat until garlic turns light brown.
Remove and discard.
Add green pepper and onion. Cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Add beef strips. Cook until browned.
Add bamboo shoots, salt, pepper and ginger. Dissolve bouillon granules in hot water.
Slowly add to mixture in skillet.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix well; chill and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, bananas and flour sifted with soda and salt.
Add nuts.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Add pudding and Cool Whip to pineapple.
Mix well and frost.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with water and sugar.
Add pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add 7-Up.
If desired, add sliced strawberries.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine first
9 ingredients.
Mix well.
Place heaping 1/2 cup of mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup Longhorn cheese on top and bake 10 additional minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 5 servings.

title: green tomato jam
directions: *Can use sugar-free Jell-O and Sugar Twin also.

title: waffles (yeast) no knead
directions: Combine milk, shortening or margarine, sugar, salt and water. Cool to lukewarm with the water.
Add yeast.
Blend in egg.
Add sifted flour.
Mix until dough is well blended and soft.
Bake on heated waffle iron.
Makes 6 waffles.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, frozen veggies, onion soup mix and sugar.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Beat potatoes, shortening and sugar together until well blended.
Dissolve baking soda in milk; add to potato mixture. Sift flour and salt together; add to potato mixture.
Roll out 1 inch thickness on floured board.
