Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add to pie crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add topping when cool and refrigerate.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a hard boil in heavy pan. Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Add the quick oats, crunchy peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Stir.
Drop onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: no-weep meringue
directions: Mix water and cornstarch together and cook until thick and clear.
Set aside in covered pan until cool.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat in the cooled cornstarch mixture.
Top pie.
Seal to edge.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: chicken in dumpling
directions: Wash chicken.
Put in large pot.
Bring chicken to a boil. Add mushroom soup, salt and pepper, then let it simmer for 45 minutes until 1 hour.
Serves 6 or more.

title: homemade big bubbles
directions: Combine, shake and let settle for 4 hours.
Store covered in refrigerator to extend shelf life.
Allow to warm before using. Use Joy or Dawn only!

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oats and peanut butter together in bowl.
In saucepan, mix sugar, Pet milk and cocoa.
Cook until it boils for 1 minute. Quickly add vanilla and pour into oat mixture.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: baked shrimp-crab salad casserole
directions: Combine green pepper, onion and celery.
Remove tendons from crabmeat and flake.
Remove veins from shrimp and cut into pieces. Mix well crab and shrimp with vegetables.
Add mayonnaise and seasoning.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Cover top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until top is nicely browned, about 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: candy cookies
directions: Heat chips over hot water; stir until dissolved.
Add peanut butter; stir until blended.
Add Special K; mix until all are coated.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Chill.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine sugar, oatmeal, eggs and milk.
Mix well. Add butter and syrup.
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine hamburger, eggs, salt and Spanish rice.
Mix well. Put in baking dish.
Top with ketchup or barbecue sauce.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow bars
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix the next 4 ingredients with butter mixture.
Spread in a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over pan, then return to oven for 2 minutes.
Spread with knife dipped in water.
Let cool.
Cook over low heat melted the chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Put Rice Krispies in last.
Spread over bars.
Refrigerate.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: marinated green bean bundles
directions: Rinse beans; drain in
colander.
Secure
9 to 10 beans with 1/2 strip bacon and
a round toothpick.
Place bundles in an oblong Pyrex or 9 x
13-inch
pan
(a
single layer).
Make marinade of melted butter,
brown
sugar,
garlic salt and soy sauce.
Spoon marinade over each bundle (use all of marinade). Cover
with foil and
refrigerate
overnight.
Bring
to
room temperature and bake uncovered at
for 25 to 30 minutes. Bacon should look cooked.
(May
have
to
bake
in two pans.) Yields 28 to 32.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients well. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Mix again before serving. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: etouffee
directions: Melt butter; add flour, onions, celery, peppers and garlic. Add tomatoes and cook 20 minutes.
Add soup and meat.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and green onions.
Simmer 5 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves about 6.

title: mom's rolled sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll and cut out.
Place on cookie sheet.
Grease cookie sheet first time in oven.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Cut onion and pepper in rings or slice.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; slowly bring to simmer over medium heat.
Remove and pour over carrots, onion and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve cold.
Will keep for 3 weeks.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Bring to boil all but the cucumbers and onions and pour over cucumbers and onions.
Stir mixture; let cool.
Put in gallon jug. Keep in refrigerator.

title: vegetable pickles
directions: Add 1/2 cup salt over vegetables and cover with ice and ice water for 2 hours.
Drain well.
Bring other ingredients to a boil and add the vegetables.
Heat to a boil and pack in hot jars.
(Do not boil pickles.)

title: crescent cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll each marshmallow in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place one marshmallow inside one crescent roll and close as good as possible. Roll crescent roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place rolls in a muffin pan and bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Take out of muffin pans and let cool. Glaze with icing.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Combine oleo, flour, pecans and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and whipped topping.
Mix until smooth.
Pour mixture over cooled crust and top with pie filling. Chill and cut into squares before serving.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut a pocket into each chicken breast. Salt and pepper to taste; set aside.
Thoroughly drain and squeeze any liquid from thawed spinach.
Do not cook.
Combine Feta cheese, mayonnaise and garlic.
Stuff into chicken breast pockets.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening and beaten eggs.
Add soda, salt, cream of tartar, nuts and flour.
Make into rolls and refrigerate. Slice off and bake in 350° oven.

title: butterscotch pie filling
directions: Boil brown sugar, 1 cup water, vanilla and butter until taffy thickness.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell and top with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Remove from stove. Add peanut butter and beat it until it starts to thicken. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in buttered pan. Cool and cut.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Bread and fry chicken.
In your pan (9 x 13-inch works fine) layer sauce, chicken, sauce, Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes (until cheese melts).

title: barbecued beans
directions: Combine ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low about 4 hours.
Goes great with macaroni and cheese and biscuits.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cook together for 10 minutes.
Seal in jars.
Makes 6 pints.

title: no-bake brownies
directions: Put chips and Pet milk in bowl and melt them together in microwave.
In another bowl mix vanilla wafers, marshmallows, powdered sugar and salt.
Crush wafers until only crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 cup of chocolate mixture for glaze.
Stir rest of mixture over crumb mixture. Mix well.
Press into buttered 9-inch square pan. Put 2 tablespoons of Pet milk into reserved chocolate mixture and stir.
Spread over brownies.
Chill overnight.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown beef in oil.
When thoroughly browned, saute garlic and onion until onion is translucent.
Add beef broth, tomato sauce, peppercorns, cloves and bay leaves.
Simmer until meat is tender. After simmering 1/2 hour, add wine and simmer for another half hour or until meat is tender.
Then add the potatoes, carrots and celery.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: potato patties
directions: Mix all together.
Put oil or bacon grease in heavy skillet and heat on medium.
Drop mixture by tablespoons into oil, lower heat and fry until brown on both sides.

title: fruit salad
directions: Blend dry pudding and Tang together.
Add juice from pineapple.
Mix with fruit and chill.
Just before serving, add banana.

title: lemon bars(for kids)
directions: Mix flour, powdered sugar, butter and salt together (it will be crumbly) and pat the mixture into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
While this is baking, mix eggs, sugar, flour and lemon juice.
Pour over the "crust" while hot.
Return to oven and bake 25 minutes more.
Remove from oven, cool for 15 minutes, then cut into squares.
Makes about 20 squares.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt margarine; add nuts, brown sugar and flour.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until brown.
Cool.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream margarine, brown sugar, white sugar, peanut butter, egg, vanilla and milk.
Add remaining ingredients until moist.
Mix well.
Roll into balls, then roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While cookies are still warm, place one chocolate kiss in center.

title: good morning pumpkin pancakes
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine biscuit mix, sugar, cinnamon, and allspice.
Add evaporated milk, pumpkin, oil, eggs, and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour 1/4 to 1/2 cup batter onto heated griddle.
Cook until top surface is bubbly and edges are dry. Turn, cook until golden.
Keep pancakes warm.
Serve with syrup or honey.
Makes about 16 pancakes.

title: vegetable butter topping
directions: In a 1-cup measure, combine the butter, parsley, chives, salt and pepper.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/4 minutes or until the butter melts.
Stir in the Parmesan cheese.
Serve topping over hot cooked vegetables.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add sauce, beans, tomatoes, corn and taco seasoning.
Add water to desired consistency.
Heat to boil.
Top with grated cheese, corn chips and sour cream.

title: patsy's "i don't know" cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until done.

title: old-fashioned spiced pound cake
directions: Blend spices and salt with butter or margarine.
Gradually add sugar, mixing well after each addition.
Beat in 5 eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition, until completely blended.
Stir in flour all at one time.
Beat in the remaining egg.
Turn into a well-greased lightly floured 9 x 3-inch tube cake pan.
Place in a cold oven.
Set oven control to 300°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 20 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack to finish cooling.
Frost with Confectioners Sugar Glaze.

title: glazed beef
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Push to outer edges of skillet.
Add garlic and saute.
Stir in water and soy sauce.
Bring to hard boil.
Cover. Simmer 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook over medium-high heat until liquid is gone and beef is glazed.
Stir often so all sides of beef pieces are coated.
Serve with rice and broccoli.

title: maple syrup oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat oleo, syrup and egg together. Mix salt baking powder, and flour together. Mix dry ingredients and soft ingredients together. Add milk, mix well, add raisins. Grease cookie sheet, drop by teaspoonfuls. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Put chicken breasts in pan with enough water to cover.
Add vegetables and let cook until chicken is tender.
Serve with cooked fine egg noodles or rice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend all together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: john's favorite
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts.

Press into pan. Bake at 350° until starting to brown. Cream the cheese and sugar and mix thoroughly. Fold in 1 cup whipped topping. Spread over the flour crust. Prepare pudding as directed. Do not chill.
Spread this on cheese layer.
Spoon on cherry topping.
Chill several hours.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in large long baking dish. Bake 1 hour or until lightly browned on top.

title: peanut logs
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add Rice Krispies and shape into logs or balls.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Melt remaining ingredients in double boiler.
Dip peanut logs into chocolate and let cool on wax paper.

title: sonbokkles(cookies)
directions: Mix well together.
Press into tins.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Combine ingredients and shape into one-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. These can be frozen before baking.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix ingredients like pie crust.
Put combined mixture in bottom of square pan (8 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch) and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash and remove the seeds from the green peppers.
Place the peppers in boiling water for 7 minutes or until tender.
Brown the meat.
While the meat is browning, add the tomatoes.
When the meat is browned, add the prepared rice.
Add the minced celery and minced onion to the cooked meat/rice mixture.
Stuff the green peppers with the meat/rice mixture and place in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until the rice begins to brown.

title: chicken pecan
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in evaporated milk and roll in dry mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush wafers with a rolling pin.
Mix sugar, margarine, eggs and half of the wafers.
Add
milk
and
mix
well.
Add remaining wafers, coconut, cherries
and pecans.
Mix well and pour into well-greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour and 10 minutes.
Let stand until almost cold before removing cake.
This cake
is
very
moist,
needing no frosting.
It can be frozen.

title: thick peach shake
directions: Process peaches, milk, sweetener and flavoring in a blender. Add ice cubes, one at a time, and blend at high speed.
The drink will be quite thick.

title: apple-lime cooler
directions: Beat sherbet until smooth.
Add apple juice gradually and blend.
Serve in chilled glasses with a cherry or lime slice. Serves two.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, cream cheese and sugar.
Add 2 eggs and 1 cup flour at a time, creaming after each addition.
Add flavoring and pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: homemade noodles(easy to divide recipe)
directions: Roll dough out as thin as possible.
Cut into strips, dry. Cook in soups or dishes, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, cheese, onions, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until topping is brown.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken breasts and onion in
a small amount of oil. Drain oil.
Add mushrooms and pizza sauce.
You may want to add water to sauce to thin.
Cook spaghetti.
Serve with Italian bread.
Serves 6.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut all vegetables into large chunks or slices.
Put in large bowl and set aside.
In small bowl, mix garlic, olive oil, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Pour garlic mixture over vegetables and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 400° on nonstick pan. Stir and rotate vegetables on pan every 20 minutes for 1 hour or until browned.

title: canned beets
directions: Heat all of this together until very hot.
Put in jars and seal.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Brown beef.
Add sauce and simmer a few minutes.
Mix eggs and cottage cheese.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish. (For ease of cleaning, line dish with foil.)
Top each piece with a slice of cheese.
In small bowl, stir in soup and water.
Spoon evenly over chicken.
Coarsely crush stuffing mix and sprinkle over chicken.
Drizzle evenly with melted butter.
Bake uncovered 350° for 45 minutes or until meat in thickest portion is no longer pink when slashed.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil cocoa, sugar and milk for 3 minutes, then add butter, peanut butter and quick oats.
Stir until peanut butter is melted. Drop on wax paper.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form into a loaf shape on baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix flour and seasonings; coat chicken with mixture.
Heat fat in large frypan.
Fry chicken until browned on one side.
Turn and brown the other side.
Continue to cook slowly, uncovered, on top of range, 30 to 45 minutes or in the oven at 350° until tender.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Cut tops off of peppers.
Remove seeds and membrane.
Precook pepper cups in boiling salted water about 5 minutes; drain.
(For crisp peppers, omit precooking.) Sprinkle inside of cups generously with salt.
Cook ground beef and onion until meat is lightly browned.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, water, rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Stuff peppers, stand upright in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt
margarine
in
saucepan.	Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add
asparagus
liquid to milk to make 1/2 cup.
Stir in flour
mixture.
Blend
until
smooth.
Cook
sauce
for
2 minutes.
Layer
asparagus	in bottom of greased 2 quart dish. Sprinkle half of crumbs over asparagus.
Add eggs and half the sauce.
Add remaining crumbs and sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown sirloin and onion.
Drain. Pour into a crock-pot.
Empty all cans with their juices into crock-pot. Add dressing mix and taco seasoning mix. Stir. Cook on low overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Stir sugars and water in saucepan until well dissolved.
Add syrup.
Cook to 252°, hard ball stage.
Pour slowly over beaten whites.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy and piles without spreading.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Coat with dipping chocolate if desired.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, milk and melted margarine; stir well.
Fold in bread crumbs and pineapple with juice; mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried bananas
directions: Peel bananas; set aside for 15 minutes.
Blend together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add slowly to the cold water, beaten egg and coconut milk.
Heat oil in wok.
Reduce heat; slip bananas into batter.
Slide in carefully, 3 at a time.
Turn over once.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Coconut is optional.

title: butter balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except sugar.
Form into balls and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Roll in sugar while still hot. Place on rack to cool before storage.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind cranberries and combine with marshmallows and sugar. Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes, pecans and salt. Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Serve in a large bowl or individual lettuce cups.
Garnish with clusters of red and green grapes, if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: turkey sandwich
directions: Put slice of tomato and turkey on each roll.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over turkey and broil until brown.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well; press most of the water out.
Mix softened butter and cream cheese; combine with spinach.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with desired amount of Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° until heated through. Can be used as an appetizer or a side dish.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, powdered cocoa and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Beat well; then fold in 1 teaspoon baking soda, dissolved in 1 tablespoon vinegar.
(It will fizz.)
Bake in two 9-inch greased and floured pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork(china)
directions: Beat the eggs and dry ingredients.
Dice the pork and mix it in.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil; deep fry.
Cook until golden brown 5 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake the cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When it cools, poke holes in the cake with a fork.
Pour the Eagle Brand milk over the cake.
Next, spread the crushed pineapple over the top.
Mix all but 1/4 of the cup of coconut with the Cool Whip.
Spread the Cool Whip over the cake, then sprinkle the remaining coconut on top. Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
Cake must be kept refrigerated.
This is a cool, creamy delicious cake that is guaranteed to disappear!
Dig in!

title: bread dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Use loaf pan.
Serve hot or cold with butter.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Set oven to 400°.
Cream together shortening, brown sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in rolled oats, oat and honey natural cereal, raisins and nuts.

title: sitting pretties
directions: Blend butter and sugar in a bowl.
Stir in egg yolks and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt into a bowl.
Mix.
Chill 1 hour.

title: crock-pot meat
directions: Place roast in crock-pot; salt and pepper.
Cook on high for 8 hours.
(I put it on at bedtime.) Remove roast and all broth.
Cut meat into small pieces (the roast usually falls apart because it is so tender).
Add one cup of broth; add all 3 mixes.
Stir well until lumps are gone.
Add meat.
Add broth in until the roast is covered by gravy mixture (about 3 cups).
Cook 2 to 3 more hours in crock-pot on low.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix all other ingredients and combine with dry.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured coffee cans (if available) or use loaf pans.
Fill a little over half full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: reuben tarts
directions: Blend cream cheese, butter and flour.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into small balls and place in ungreased 1 3/4 inch muffin cups. Press dough on bottom and sides.
Mix mayonnaise, chilli sauce, kraut, corn beef and Swiss cheese and fill cups.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 300° until brown.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: three corn casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Mix well the butter, sour cream and egg in a large bowl.
Stir in the cans of corn and muffin mix. Spoon it into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 1 hour.
If you decide to use the cheese, add it after 45 minutes and stir well. The dish is cooked when it is slightly puffed.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, well beaten egg, molasses and then the sour milk, to which soda has been added.
Sift flour and ginger together.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake in a moderate oven.

title: fresh rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in rhubarb.
Toss gently to coat fruit.
Let mixture set for 15 minutes.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Turn rhubarb mixture into pastry-lined pie plate.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Cut slits in top crust. Place pastry atop filling.
Seal and flute edges.
Bake pie in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: In dish, place apples.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon.
Mix in separate bowl by hand the remaining ingredients.
Cover apples with mixture in "patches."
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef in frypan.
Drain off grease.
Mix potatoes, soups and ground beef in frypan.
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Cook covered.

title: breaded chicken steaks
directions: Put margarine in skillet.
Add seasoning and saute lightly. Take chicken, bread crumbs and seasonings that are sauteed and add all together with egg and broth to form patties.
These may be used now or frozen individually for a later date.
Thaw slightly before frying.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown meat.
Drain and add onions.
Cook until tender.
Stir in beans, French dressing, water and chili powder.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add 4 ounces cheese.
Put mixture over lettuce and toss.
Add the remaining cheese before serving.

title: lobster or crab meat snack
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on 1/2 ham roll or English muffin.
Place an American cheese slice on top.
Melt cheese under broiler.

title: butterscotch carrot cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time. Mix flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and ground cloves. Add to creamed mixture alternately with butterscotch chips and 1/2 cup water; mix well. Stir in carrots, raisins and applesauce. Pour into 2 waxed paper lined 8-inch round pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: brown sugar icing
directions: Add melted butter and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in milk. Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Cool to lukewarm. Beat in powdered sugar.
Makes enough to do a 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch cake.

title: cherry or blueberry delight
directions: Place crumbs in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar, whipped cream, lemon juice and vanilla; pour over crust.
Place fruit topping on top of cream mixture. Refrigerate and cut into squares and serve.

title: raisin apple coffee cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar and egg.
Add milk, then flour sifted together with baking powder and salt.
Stir in raisins.
Spread on greased and floured square pan, 9 x 9.
Arrange thinly sliced apples over the batter; press in slightly.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixed with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together in baking dish.
Bake on 350° for 45 minutes. Do not cover dish.

title: instant rice dressing
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Place in well-greased baking dish
or
pan with tight fitting cover.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Salt and pepper are optional because the condensed soup is
used undiluted and is well seasoned.
This recipe serves 8 to 10 people.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Pour in a large casserole.
Melt butter in dish.
Take 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/2 stick butter. Put on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and almond flavoring.
Next, add flour.
Mix well.
Chill for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: In a food processor, grate cheese.
Mix other ingredients in processor.
Store in airtight container.

title: veggie reuben sandwich
directions: Toast the bread.
Spread with mustard.
Split the Tempeh horizontally and saute both sides in oil.
Place Tempeh on the bread and add the sauerkraut.
Top with slice of cheese.
Place in toaster oven or microwave to melt cheese.

title: lake murray pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into graham crusts and refrigerate until firm. Yields 2 pies or 12 servings.

title: dream frozen fruit salad
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix by package directions and set aside.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and plain flour.
Mix with berries and pineapple and set aside.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Take off fire.
Add oats and peanut butter.
Add vanilla. Stir and drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Set the first 2 ingredients aside to cool.
Cream Crisco and sugar well; add egg yolks one at a time.
Add cooled chocolate mixture.
Add milk and flour alternately using with flour.
Add egg whites.
Add to batter 1 cup coconut and cup pecans (optional).
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: molded cottage cheese waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into individual molds.
Chill until firm.

title: quick vegetable casserole
directions: Mix well.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cook in casserole dish until it bubbles on top.
Add biscuits on top and cook until done and brown.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Use 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.

title: zesty mango sauce(low-fat)
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine mango and lemon juice; cover and blend until smooth.
Cut several thin slices from onion; reserve for garnish.
Chop remaining onion.
In a skillet, combine mango mixture, onion, pineapple, tomato, bouillon granules, chili powder, and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 4 to 5 minutes or until onion is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve over grilled fish or seafood. Makes 3 1/4 cups.
Per 1/2 cup serving, 0 gram fat.

title: white chili
directions: Boil chicken (skin off).
Mix all ingredients in saucepan. Cook until onions are done, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, carrots, sour cream, green pepper and soup. Separately mix butter and stuffing, adding water to desired moistness.
In casserole dish put half of stuffing on bottom, squash mixture and half of stuffing on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna rice bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup and milk.
Add tuna, vegetables and cooked rice; stir gently to mix. Bake 20 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Stir.
Makes 4 cups.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of celery soup

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine and water.
In a large bowl, mix together cocoa, sugar, flour and salt.
Pour hot mixture into sifted ingredients.
Add eggs, soda and sour cream.
Mix well. Pour into greased flat cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken amaretto
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch wide strips.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic powder and curry powder.
Roll strips in flour. Heat margarine in a large skillet.
Brown chicken pieces on all sides.
Add mushrooms, Amaretto and lemon juice; simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix chicken broth and cornstarch together.
Pour mixture into skillet; stir over low heat, until mixture bubbles and thickens.
Spoon mixture over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homestyle vegetable soup
directions: Start by cooking hamburger or ground chuck until done. If using a steak, cook in a crock-pot for about 4 hours until done. In a stockpot, put in tomato juice and add your mixed vegetables; next, your lima beans. Stir it all together. Next, put in your dash of black pepper and your Worcestershire sauce. Let cook about 5 minutes. Very delicious.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and divide the dough in half for 2 crusts.
Place the bottom crust in a 9-inch pie plate.

title: strawberry dessert sauce
directions: Puree whole strawberries with apple juice in a food processor or blender.
Stir in sliced strawberries and gently fold in yogurt.
Serve over waffles or any dessert.

title: yankee corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine milk, oil and eggs.
Combine and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 2 cups corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped broccoli
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Combine all ingredients except stuffing mix in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with 1/3 package of stuffing. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Mix all the other ingredients together.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into well buttered pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: oatmeal crackers(havrekjeks)
directions: Mix corn and bran flakes and then crush.
Add oats, flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add.
Blend well.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts. On a floured pastry cloth, roll each portion to 1/16-inch thick, using a sleeve-covered lefse rolling pin.
With a pizza or fattigman cutter, cut into 2 x 3-inch rectangles.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool. Crackers are tender, so store carefully.

title: old fashion banana  pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Bring to a boil, reduce to medium heat.
Stir constantly until thickened, but not to thick.
In a large bowl layer vanilla wafers and bananas. Repeat this procedure until bowl is full.
Pour pudding over layers.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, 1 egg, nuts and butter by hand and spread mixture in a sheet cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs; pour this mixture over the first mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cheese while hot and beat until creamy. Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and set.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except Velveeta cheese.
Pour in casserole.
Top with Velveeta.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bologna spread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Spread on 6 slices of bologna.
Stack bologna slices on top of each other.
Wrap in plastic wrap and store in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in pie shape wedges.

title: easy bran refrigerated muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients, including nuts, if desired.
In second bowl, beat eggs well. Add oil and buttermilk to eggs.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well, but only until all ingredients are thoroughly blended.
Put in refrigerator in tightly covered container.
(Will keep up to 6 weeks.)
Fill muffin tins half full of batter.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes.
I use a 5-quart ice cream pail to mix in and store batter in.

title: just like fried ice cream
directions: Using a large ice cream scoop, make four 1/2-cup scoops of ice cream.
Place in a shallow pan.
Cover and store in the freezer until firm.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well.
Add melted butter and lemon juice.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake 1 hour at 350° or until middle is set and pie is brown.
Cool and serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and add next 6 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and add baby carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Stir only to mix.
Bake in 11 x 16-inch pan (13 x 9-inch for thicker cake).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs.
Layer eggs between mixture in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with slices of American cheese and bake another 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Cream butter, cream cheese and vanilla. Add sugar, cream until light.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each.
Add flour and baking powder.
Grease and flour bundt pan.
Put cake in cold oven.
Set for 275 degrees and cook for 1 1/2 hour.

title: super supper casserole
directions: Brown meat; pour off fat.
Combine meat, potato slices and broccoli in casserole.
Sprinkle with dry sauce mix from potato package.
Mix milk and mayonnaise and pour over casserole along with boiling water.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Mix melted margarine with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole; bake another 15 to 20 minutes, until potatoes are tender.

title: lemon cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups of hot water.
Thaw berries and add juice, berries and sauce to the mixture.

title: corn bread cake
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients and pour in baking dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: potato soup with instant potatoes
directions: Heat butter, onions, salt, celery salt, pepper and milk to scalding.
Stir in potatoes.
Continue cooking until smooth, stirring constantly.
Soup should be consistency of heavy cream. Garnish with red pepper and parsley.

title: walnut bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth.
At low speed, stir in flour mixture.
Fold in walnuts, vanilla and sour cream.
Turn batter into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes, then invert onto wire rack.

title: anita's chicken in a garden
directions: Combine chicken, thawed vegetables, soup, milk and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Top with remaining onions. Cook a few minutes longer.

title: garlic roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine oil, lemon peel, salt, pepper, rosemary, potatoes, garlic, onions and red pepper in large bowl; toss to coat well.
Spread in a jelly roll pan.
Roast 40 to 45 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mix fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar. Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts. Mix well and freeze. Let thaw for 20 minutes before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl, whisk eggs until frothy.
Whisk in milk, syrup, orange peel and 1/4 teaspoon of salt; set aside.
Quarter 3 slices of bread.
Cut remaining into 1-inch squares.
Dip bread quarters into milk mixture.
Arrange, points up around side of greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Soak bread cubes and currants in milk mixture 5 minutes.
Pour bread cubes, currants and any milk mixture into casserole.
Place in roasting pan in middle of oven. Pour boiling water into pan to halfway up side of casserole.
Bake 70 minutes at 325° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mamma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar, oil or oleo and vanilla.
Add the flour, salt and baking powder. Combine ingredients.
Use teaspoon. Drop onto greased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Dip the bottom of a water glass in water or oil, then sugar and flatten the cookie dough. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine until tender.
Combine onion mixture in a bowl with chopped chicken and green chili peppers; set aside.
For sauce, in the same saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Stir in flour, coriander and salt.
Stir in chicken broth all at once; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Stir 1/2 cup of sauce into the chicken mixture.
Dip each tortilla into remaining sauce to soften; fill each with about 1/4 cup of chicken mixture. Roll up.
Arrange rolls in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; pour remaining sauce over.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven about 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix cherries and glaze together and pour into crust. Chill for 3 hours.
Serve with ice cream.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Cook peppers and onions together until onions are clear.
Add corned beef and barbecue sauce.
Heat about 15 minutes.
Serve on bun with cole slaw.

title: baked beef brisket
directions: Put the brisket into a 9 x 13-inch pan, fat side up. Pour vinegar over the top. Cover top of the brisket heavily with the garlic salt, salt, pepper, paprika, Lawry's seasoned salt, Accent and parsley. Slice the onion over the top of the meat. Add 1/2 cup of water. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes until brown. Reduce heat to 325° and add 1 1/2 cups of boiling water. Cover with foil. Bake until tender, about 3 1/2 to 4 hours. Refrigerate overnight. Slice cross-grain very thinly. Put back in juices and reheat. Makes fantastic sandwiches.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk until it falls apart.
Mix in salt, pepper, onion, allspice and eggs; mix well.
Add hamburg.
Mix with hands. Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° until cooked through.
Make gravy with pan drippings and canned beef broth.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Add balance of ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with the following:
Fritos corn chips, chopped onions, diced tomatoes, shredded lettuce, sour cream and salsa.

title: spinach salad
directions: Pick over the spinach and remove any tough stems and blemished leaves.
Tear into small pieces.
Fry the bacon until crisp and crumble.
Slice the boiled eggs.
Place the spinach in a serving bowl and top with the sliced eggs.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix vegetables together.
Add about 1/4 cup mayonnaise.
Too much will make salad soupy.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet cheese fritters(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Drain the cheese of all its moisture by setting it in a colander, covering it with a kitchen towel, and weighting it with a heavy casserole.
Let the cheese drain undisturbed for 2 or 3 hours, then with the back of a spoon, rub it through a fine sieve set over a bowl.
Beat in the egg yolks, one at a time, and gradually beat in the flour, salt and sugar.
Shape the mixture into 4 equal balls.

title: wilson's sour cream blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and granulated sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Add this flour mixture gradually to the egg mixture, alternating with sour cream.
End with the flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla and cardamom. Fold in 1 cup blueberries.
Pour half the batter into a well-greased and floured 9x13x2 inch pan.
Cover with remaining blueberries.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 325 degrees for 50 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool slightly and slice.

title: steak and mushroom gravy
directions: Combine flour and seasonings on wax paper.
Pound into meat which is cut into serving size pieces.
Brown in 2 tablespoons of hot oil.
Remove from skillet; drain fat and wipe pan.
Combine soup and water in skillet.
Put meat into soup mixture and simmer until meat is tender.
Stir in sour cream and heat.
Do not boil; sour cream will curdle.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: pasta with shrimp in wine sauce
directions: Cook pasta and drain, reserving 1/4 cup pasta cooking liquid. In large nonstick skillet, cook shrimp, spinach and garlic in oil over medium-high heat until shrimp are pink (about 2 to 3 minutes). Add wine, seasonings and pasta cooking liquid.
Cover, reduce heat to medium-low and cook 2 minutes longer.
Place pasta in serving dish.
Pour shrimp sauce over pasta and toss.

title: mexicali mary
directions: Brown onion in small amount of oil. Brown ground chuck. Add other ingredients.
Let cheese melt over ingredients. Add taco chips and mix.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Smash cookies and add butter.
Save 1 cup of Oreos for top.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except Sprite.
Add the Sprite just before serving.
You may add just a little Kool-Aid for the color that is desired.

title: opal's icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water; set aside.
Combine sugar and shortening in 2 cups warm water.
Add 3 cups flour and yeast; mix well.
Then add remaining flour, mix well and let rise until approximately doubled in bulk.
Then place on floured board and work down, then pinch off and use as needed.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: minute steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat steak with flour mixture. Heat shortening in skillet and add the coated steak.
Brown on one side, turn over and brown.
Pour about 1 cup water over the steak and cover.
Let cook over low heat until cooked down to gravy.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Pound chicken slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil and butter in skillet.
Cook chicken in skillet over high heat for 3 minutes on each side. Remove chicken and keep warm.
Add chives/onions, lime/lemon juice, brandy, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth. Whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken. Serve.

title: lemon crumb squares
directions: Blend together milk, juice and rind of lemon. Set aside. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Cream butter and blend in sugar. Add flour mixture and oatmeal; mix until crumbly. Spread half the mixture in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Pat the mixture down and spread condensed milk mixture over it. Cover top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown around edges (about 25 minutes).
Cool in pan at room temperature for 15 minutes. Cut into 1 3/4 inch squares and chill in pan until firm. Yields 2 dozen.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Put drained, fried sausage in bottom of casserole dish. Spread vegetable soup over this.
Prepare mashed potatoes (just like you are preparing them for a vegetable dish for a meal). Spread on top of sausage and vegetable soup.
Bake in oven until potatoes are brown (not real brown) and soup is bubbling.

title: pineapple or peach upside-down cake
directions: Put margarine in 9 or 10-inch skillet and melt.
Add brown sugar.
Arrange fruit on top.
Beat sugar and eggs until very light.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until very light and foamy. Pour over first part.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes. When done, turn over on a large plate.
Fruit will be on top.

title: ziti with pepperoni
directions: In a large frying pan, slowly fry the pepperoni.
Add some olive oil (enough to spread across the bottom of the pan) and some chopped garlic.
When the pepperoni starts to cook, add the beef broth.
Stir, then add the tomato paste.
Get all of this to simmer, adding the half and half to give the sauce a pinkish color (don't use the whole pint).
Add a little parsley, oregano and rosemary for flavor.
Add the chopped olives and stir.
Let simmer. After cooking the macaroni, put it in a large platter about 18 x 12 x 1 1/2-inches.
Pour the sauce on top of macaroni and serve. Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: chicken-spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix.
Place in a 10 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup of shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Freezes well.

title: chicken with gravy
directions: In a bowl, mix soups and sherry.
Place chicken in a lightly greased baking dish; salt and pepper chicken and pour soup mixture over it.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Serve over rice.

title: basic pizza crust
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water, stirring about 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups flour, salt and oil to make a soft dough.
On lightly floured surface, knead until smooth (about 5 minutes, add remaining flour, a little at a time, to prevent dough from sticking to hands).
Grease or coat (using a nonstick spray) a large bowl.
Place dough in the bowl, turn to coat top of dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place until it doubles in size, about 1 hour.

title: shrimp mousse dip
directions: Combine soup and cream cheese in a blender until smooth.
Put this mixture into a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased jello mold.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: irish tea scones
directions: Sieve flour, baking powder and salt.
Rub in margarine.
Add sugar and sultanas.
Mix to a soft dough with milk (not too soft). Cut out on floured board.
Brush with egg and milk; bake in hot oven (450°) for approximately 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix thoroughly and press crust in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cranberry banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pan at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: peppery dip with vegetables
directions: In small bowl, stir all ingredients except the cauliflowerets and carrots.
Cover; refrigerate.
Spoon into bowl.
Set on plate. Surround with vegetables.

title: swiss steak mozzarella
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces; coat with flour.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Brown meat slowly on both sides.
Put into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine tomatoes, salt, basil and green pepper; pour over meat.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour, or until meat is tender.
Remove cover; sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crumbled crackers.
Press into a 13 X 9 X 2 pan.
Let ice cream get soft, then mix with vanilla pudding with electric mixer for about 4
minutes.
Spoon over crackers.
Spread Cool Whip over the ice cream mixture.
Sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip, then sprinkle nuts over the coconut.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Place hamburger and all remaining ingredients in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: cocktail weenies
directions: Combine all and simmer.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: potatoes and sour cream
directions: Melt butter in pan; add soup and sour cream.
Mix together. Break up hash browns and place in a 13 x 9-inch oblong glass baking dish.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Add chopped onions and grated cheese.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diet waldorf salad
directions: Wash, core and dice apples into 1/2-inch cubes.
Add apple cubes to chopped celery and Miracle Whip with extract.
Add raisins; stir well.
Serves 6.
Has 75 calories, 2.5 grams fat, food exchanges equals 1 fruit, 1/2 vegetable and 3/4 fat.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar, cornmeal and flour.
Add beaten eggs and beat well into dry ingredients.
Add milk, butter, lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust. Bake 350°
for 40 - 45 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting. Serves 6.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix vegetable mix and sour cream.
Chop onions and chestnuts then mix spinach, onions and chestnuts in sour cream/vegetable mix.
Chill for 3 hours.
Hollow out the center of a round Hawaiian bread to use as a bowl.
Tear pieces of bread and use extra crackers for dipping pieces.

title: devil's food pudding cake
directions: Mix cake and bake as directed. Cool. Mix vanilla pudding as directed. Spread on top.
Mix chocolate pudding as directed and spread on top of vanilla. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle pecans on top.
Leave in pan and refrigerate.

title: lemon or pistachio dessert
directions: Mix all together and put on top of other layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cool in fridge for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for two minutes.
Start counting the time when the mixture has reached a full boil. Remove from heat and add oats, nuts, peanut butter and vanilla. Spoon onto wax paper when mixture is cooled.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except green chilies and cheese. Pour half the batter into a greased 13 x 9 pan and cover with sliced cheese and green chilies.
Cover with remaining batter. Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven until set.

title: farmer's cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Make into 2 rolls. Wrap in wax paper. Chill overnight. Slice and bake 10 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in Pam sprayed skillet (or 2 tablespoons butter).
Fry until brown and turn.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine the milk, chocolate and butter. Cook and stir over medium-low heat until chocolate is melted. Remove from the heat; stir in vanilla. Yield: About 1 1/2 cups.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all of the above well and pour into 2 pie shells and bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped walnuts over mixture in pan.
Blend egg whites and brown sugar.
Pour over the chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together and chill.
Beat together the rest of the ingredients and spread on top of chilled mixture.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday punch slush
directions: Make strong tea with 3 tea bags.
Combine all other ingredients and mix.
Freeze in Tupperware.
Ready to serve in 24 hours.
To serve, fill glass 1/2 full with slush and 1/2 full with 7-Up or Sprite.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Brown the meat in oil.
Put in bottom of crock-pot.
Layer raw vegetables over meat.
Mix soups, water, sugar, tapioca, soy sauce and salt and pepper.
Pour mixture in top of crock-pot.
Cook on low all day.
If cooked on high, done in 4 to 5 hours.

title: bean salad
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Drain juice from corn, sweet peas and green beans.
Mix with onion and bell pepper.
Add vinegar mixture.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: avocado shrimp salad
directions: Peel and chop avocados.
Gently mix avocado, shrimp, mandarins and sliced red onion.
Arrange on bed of butter lettuce, dress with Nut Dressing, top with alfalfa sprouts.
Serves 4.

title: slaw and noodles
directions: Break Ramen noodles into small pieces; add slaw and onions.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil and seasoning mix to make dressing.
Pour over slaw mixture.
Chill overnight, stirring 2 to 3 times.
Garnish with sunflower seeds.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a large pot, saute vegetables in margarine.
Slowly add flour.
Parboil broccoli.
Add water and all to vegetables.
Add chicken broth and potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cheese may also be added.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix in flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into Bundt pan (greased and floured).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: strawberry spoon dessert drink
directions: To prepare pineapple, cut off both ends.
Remove rind and eyes with sharp knife.
Cut pineapple into lengthwise quarters.
Remove core; cut fruit into chunks.
Measure 1 cup pineapple; reserve remaining pineapple for another use.
Place 1 cup pineapple and strawberries in large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Let stand until ready to use.
Divide fruit among 4 glasses; add 1/2 cup sherbet to each glass.
Pour 1 cup ginger ale into each glass.
Serve immediately.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Cut the English muffins in half, then use a spoon to spread sauce over muffins.
Add pepperoni and cheeses on top of sauce.
Put in oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Take out and serve.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Add coffee and 1/2 cup water.
Let cool.
Add vodka or brandy and the vanilla bean.
Let stand at least 6 days.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Squeeze all water out of spinach.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Keeps well for several days.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Combine all ingredients: blend well. Pour into ice cream freezer. Makes 1 gallon.

title: pound cake
directions: Put
all
ingredients
(except nuts, if using) in large bowl; beat well for 15
minutes.	Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.	Do
not preheat oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: fruit bread
directions: Mix sugar, bananas, eggs, pineapple and cherries.
Mix with oil.
Mix flour, salt and soda and add to mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300°.

title: creamy dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart (16 x 6-inch) pan in oven.
Sprinkle in crumbs. Stir well.
Press on bottom of pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain and mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 5.

title: bologna on a stick
directions: Remove rind from bologna.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Cut English muffins into 1-inch cubes.
Alternate cubes of meat and cubes of muffins on skewers.

title: instant dip mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small lidded jar.
Store the mix made with commercially grated Parmesan at room temperature.
If you use fresh grated Parmesan, store in refrigerator.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, lemon rind, juice, egg yolks and milk in heavy saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thick. Stir in butter.
Cool mixture to room temperature.
Stir in sour cream and pour into pie shell. Top with whipped cream and garnish.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms. Snap out and chop the stems. Combine the chopped stems, butter and onion. Microwave for 3 minutes or until the onion is tender. Stir in most of the cheese (reserve a little to top the mushrooms) and microwave for 1 minute. Stir in the bread crumbs, garlic salt and crab. Fill the mushroom caps with the crab mixture. Arrange on a plate. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and microwave for 5 minutes.

title: hawaiian sweet bread(also known as portuguese sweet bread)
directions: In small pan, beat instant potatoes into boiling water. Stir in sugar, dry milk, and margarine.	Let cool to 110°.
In large bowl,
dissolve
yeast
in	warm water.
Blend in cooled potato mixture.
Add
2 cups flour and beat to blend.
Stir in eggs, salt
and
vanilla	until
blended	smoothly.
Beat
in another 1 1/2 cups flour.

title: hot sauce fried chicken
directions: In a large bowl, season cut-up chicken with garlic powder and salt.
Add hot sauce.
Stir well.
Stir in enough flour to coat the chicken well.
Dip each piece of chicken in dry flour (self-rising is best).
Deep fry in hot shortening until golden brown.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes on high without cover to keep firm.
Drain potatoes.
Mix the other ingredients together in small bowl. Lightly fold in potatoes.
Do not stir.
Add more mayonnaise if needed.
Chill before serving.

title: pimento cottage cheese
directions: Cook all but cottage cheese and pimentos until thickened.
Add pimentos and let cool.
Add cottage cheese.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: creamy turkey bake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix noodles, sauce mix and remaining ingredients, except cereal in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 15 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Sprinkle with cereal.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.
Let stand uncovered about 5 minutes or until desired consistency.
Yields 5 servings.

title: granny's cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef (use very lean beef) with onions, celery and seasonings. Add thinly sliced cabbage and continue cooking for about 45 minutes. Sprinkle about 1/2 to 3/4 cup bread crumbs into mixture and continue cooking for about 15 minutes.
Put in casserole and cover top with additional bread crumbs. Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water. Freeze part of this in a ring to use in the punch bowl for ice. Add remaining ingredients and chill. Yield: 3 gallons, 50 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix together onion, enchilada sauce, chilies, tomato paste and soups; add to meat.
Cut 1 package of corn meal tortillas into bite size pieces and line casserole dish with half of tortillas.
Cover with half of mixture and rest of tortillas.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; top with 1/2 pound grated cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more, or until cheese melts.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly the flour, margarine and powdered
sugar in small bowl.
Press evenly with hands in bottom and
about 5/8-inch up sides of ungreased square pan, 8 x 8
x 2-inch
(if
dough is sticky, flour fingers).
Bake 20 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt and soda.
Add eggs, corn, milk, oleo, onion and peppers.
Mix well, then add sausage and cheese.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan or casserole dish.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes at 400° uncovered.
Makes at least 10 servings.
May be frozen.
This is a complete meal with a green salad.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. Then add Karo, vanilla and pecans.
Bake until firm in 350° oven, about 40 minutes.
It is best not to overcook.

title: cottage cheese and jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add lemon juice, evaporated milk and pineapple.
Fold in cottage cheese and pecans.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil noodles.
Place in bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix chopped chicken with noodles.
Put asparagus tips on noodle mixture.
Add soup, salt and pepper.
Put grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until moist.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and banana.
Spoon into a well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in the pan for 10 minutes.
Top with cream cheese icing.

title: margies potato salad(serves about 60)
directions: Cook potatoes and eggs, Cool.
Cut into small chunks in a large bowl.
Add onions and the thinned and mustarded Miracle Whip.
Pour over potatoes and eggs.
Stir.
Let stand a couple hours in cool place for flavor to penetrate.

title: kourambiethes(greek christmas cookies)
directions: Note:
Very quick if you use a food processor.

title: artichoke cracker spread
directions: Press crescent rolls in baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Combine other ingredients and spread over top. Bake 15 minutes.

title: baked potato and ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place potatoes, celery, onions and green pepper in water (use deep casserole dish).
Cook until tender but not all the way done.
Drain off water; add ham, cream of mushroom soup and margarine.
Put back in the oven and cook 35 to 40 minutes until done.
Just before you serve, sprinkle cheese on top.
Place back in oven until the cheese is melted.

title: chicken tezzarinna
directions: Simmer mushrooms, garlic and onion in butter.
Add flour until bubbly.
Add cream and cook.
Add cooked chicken and Mozzarella cheese.
Pour over cooked linguine or vermicelli and mix. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Ready to serve.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs with fork. Gently fold in 1/4 cup of the corn syrup, cinnamon and nutmeg until blended.
Spread evenly in pan.
Mix remaining corn syrup, walnut pieces and margarine.
Spoon evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Let cool in pan.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend well in blender.

title: cream of cabbage soup
directions: Melt butter over medium-high heat.
Add cabbage, andouille, tasso, onions, celery, green peppers, garlic and tomatoes.
Saute 20 minutes or until cabbage is wilted. Add sugar and flour. Stir constantly until white roux is achieved.
Do not let it brown. Add chicken stock, one ladle at a time, stirring constantly, until all is incorporated.
Bring to a rolling boil. Reduce heat to simmer and cook 30 minutes. Add heavy cream, shallots and parsley. Cook 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Enjoy!

title: rodgers forge chili
directions: You will need 1 large, stainless steel pot or frying pan.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken giblets and neck.
Place chicken, breast side down, in a 5-quart saucepan or Dutch pan, with one teaspoon salt and 2 inches water.
Cook on high heat until boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 35 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken.
Refrigerate 20 minutes, until easy to handle.

title: beef-and-vegetable casserole
directions: Arrange in Pyrex baking dish and bake 1 hour at 375°. Top with slices of cheese.

title: spiced fruit drink (hot)
directions: Put water in large pan; add red hots and heat until melted. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Can be refrigerated and heated as needed.

title: polenta (microwave)
directions: Whip water, corn meal and salt together until blended in 3-quart microwave bowl.
Cover, cook on High 5 minutes.
Take it out and whip until smooth, recover, cook 5 minutes, take it out again and whip.
Recover and cook 3 minutes.
Let it stand 1 minute, then whip in cheese (it will melt quickly).
Top with tomato sauce.

title: easy crock-pot roast
directions: Wash chuck roast and coat with flour. Place floured roast into oiled skillet and brown lightly on both sides. While browning roast, add diced onions to skillet. Transfer roast and onions to greased crock-pot. Pour in 1/2 can beef broth over roast and add salt and pepper. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: crepes
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender. Whirl 1 minute. Scrape sides of blender and blend for 15 seconds more.
Refrigerate batter for 1 hour.
Pour 2 to 3 tablespoons of batter into lightly buttered crepe pan, rotating pan quickly to coat bottom evenly. Cook until lightly brown.
With spatula turn crepe very carefully and brown other side. Remove crepe and cool.
Repeat for remaining crepes.

title: macaroon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Mix in large bowl.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat each addition.
Add almond extract.
Add flour to creamed mixture and beat thoroughly.
Add coconut; pour into pan.
Blend chopped almonds and sprinkle over top of loaf.
Bake for 1 hour. Cool slightly and remove from pan.
Cool and enjoy.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream well together.
Beat eggs well and fold into mixture. Scrape and mash bananas and add to mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and add, beating in quickly.
Turn into greased loaf pan and let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes. Makes one loaf.

title: potato sausage casserole
directions: Brown pork chops well, seasoning with salt and pepper.
While they are browning, peel and slice potatoes as for scalloped potatoes.
Place them in a casserole dish, sprinkling a tablespoon of flour, salt and pepper between layers.
On the top of the potatoes, place the browned pork chops.
Heat milk (about 2 cups) in the same skillet, stirring to get the brown fryings blended. Pour over the top of the potatoes.
Cover dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans for 3 hours in cold water.
Bring to boil.
Cut back heat.
Add salt, pepper, onion, and garlic.
Cook, covered, until beans are done, about 2 hours.
One-half hour before beans are done, add ham and potatoes.

title: texas tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Sift 4 cups flour, baking powder and salt together and add slowly to egg mixture.
Add flavorings.
Do this with mixer.
Stir in by hand about 2 more cups flour so the mixture will look like biscuit dough.
Roll out on floured board about 1/4-inch thick and cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheets and bake on bottom rack of preheated 400° oven for 6 minutes, then on middle rack for 6 more minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Cut up into small pieces and arrange in buttered 7 1/2 x 11-inch casserole.
Mix soup with sour cream and pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with poppy seed. Sprinkle over chicken.
Pour melted butter evenly over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dill marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate in the refrigerator overnight.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla flavoring.
Add corn and blend well.
Add milk, mix well and pour into baking dish.
After you put everything in pan, chop stick of butter in mixture and bake.

title: orange date muffins
directions: Stir and toss together 1/4 cup sugar, baking soda and salt. Beat eggs lightly in bowl.
Beat in shortening, 1/4 cup orange juice and milk.
Add remaining dry ingredients, mixing just until flour is moistened.
Batter should not be completely smooth.
Fold in dates and nuts.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Sprinkle top with the 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: rhubarb-strawberry salad
directions: Cook
rhubarb as directed on package with the sugar; let cool. Mix
Jell-O and boiling water.
Add the strawberries and rhubarb to Jell-O.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until firm. Yields 12 servings.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Simmer until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes, or place everything in crock-pot for 3 or 4 hours.
Serve with a sourdough toast and a fresh fruit salad.

title: chicken vesuvio
directions: Coat chicken pieces with mix of flour, salt and pepper. Heat 1/2
cup
oil
in
skillet, add chicken and brown on all sides. Place
in
large
baking dish.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil and	saute garlic
until
lightly
browned.
Add
Marsala and parsley; mix well.
Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 325°
about 45 minutes or until tender, turning once.
Prepare potatoes and place around baking dish.

title: punch
directions: Freeze your ice cubes with this mix.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in ball about the size of a large marble.
Bake in 400° oven for about 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 190.
These may be made ahead and frozen.

title: gingerbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, ginger, baking powder and baking soda.
Add shortening, molasses, egg and water.
Beat with an electric mixer on low to medium speed until combined.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack in the pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve warm.
Serves 9.

title: a and b's tasty chicken wings(makes 24 wings)
directions: Blend; pour over chicken wings. Allow to marinate for 6 hours or overnight.
Grill wings.
Presto!

title: florentine meat salad
directions: Place meat strips in plastic bag or bowl; add Italian dressing, turning to coat strips.
Tie bag securely or cover bowl and marinate in refrigerator 3 hours or longer.
Tear spinach into pieces and place in large salad bowl.
Drain marinade from meat, reserving marinade.
Add meat, artichoke hearts, onions and olives to spinach; toss lightly.
Add tomatoes and reserved marinade, as desired, and toss lightly to combine.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all
the ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: Brown pork ribs and set aside.
Brown onions, bell pepper, garlic, ground chuck and pork.
Combine pork ribs with mixture. Add seasonings, parsley and cooked rice.
Add chopped green onions just before serving.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift, then measure the flour.
Sift again with the baking soda and salt.
Combine sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Then add the flour, beating it until smooth.
Place the dough in a covered bowl and chill in the refrigerator overnight or several hours.
Cut out a small amount of dough and place on a lightly floured board and roll thin.
The remainder of the dough can be left in the refrigerator until time for the next baking.
Bake on an ungreased baking sheet at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dilly bread
directions: Melt butter.
Add and mix parsley, lemon juice, dill weed and cheese.
Add biscuits to butter to coat.
Place biscuits on end in Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Mix together eggs, margarine and sugar and combine both mixtures.
Add flour and vanilla.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: 20 minute apple butter
directions: In large pan combine applesauce, sugar and Kool-Aid.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently to prevent sticking.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in flavoring.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Seal at once.

title: corn medley
directions: Simmer onion and peppers in butter until soft. Add remaining ingredients and beat thoroughly.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat at high speed until smooth.
Refrigerate.
Dip your apples or other favorite fruit and enjoy.

title: oven stew
directions: Put meat and vegetables into oven casserole dish.
Mix broth and soups together.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 350°.
If desired, the last 15 minutes, add fresh broccoli flowerets.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Put spices in a tea ball or tie them in cheesecloth.
Heat slowly to no more than 170°.
Do not boil.
Let it steep while you make a snowman.

title: ann's baptist punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in cranberry juice in saucepan over low heat. Add to other juices and chill.
Pour over ice ring in a large punch bowl.
Add 7-Up just before serving.
Makes 24 (6 ounce) servings.

title: almost snickers
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and freeze.
Store in plastic bag in freezer.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread mixture evenly in a glass loaf dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at Power level 7 for 25 minutes or until center is no longer pink.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth; drain.
Saute onions and bell pepper.
Add soups, tomatoes with liquid and Velveeta.
Heat until cheese has melted.
Put spaghetti in casserole.
Place chicken on top of spaghetti.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and spaghetti. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dallas nut sandwiches
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Work in sifted flour and baking powder.
Chill dough well.
Divide dough in half and roll each half into rectangle.
Place one rectangle on a buttered baking sheet.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with nuts and sugar.
Brush other half with butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Place second 1/2 over first and press edges together.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cut into fingers while slightly warm.
Nice on a cold day with hot tea or coffee.

title: crab canapes
directions: Spray mini muffin pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Divide the dinner rolls into layers and press into cups.
Mix remaining ingredients and fill cups with 1 tablespoon of the mixture. Garnish with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Roll out bottom crust and fit into 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange apples slices in pastry shell.
Cover with top.
Make hole in center of pastry shell top, large enough for funnel.
Bake in 400° oven 30 minutes or until crust is golden.
Remove from oven.
In small saucepan, mix together margarine, cornstarch, cinnamon, salt and dark corn syrup.
Bring to a boil, boil 5 minutes.
Place funnel in hole in center of pie.
Pour corn syrup mixture through funnel, tilting pie so that mixture is evenly distributed.
Cool.

title: light vegetable soup
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Add spinach and simmer an additional 5 minutes.
Yields about 3 1/2 quarts.
Contains about 64 calories per 1 cup serving.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening very well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add syrup.
Add flour and milk alternately, small amount at a time, and beating well after each addition. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese drops
directions: Cream the margarine and cheese. Sift flour and cayenne.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in cereal. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: bittersweet chocolate delight(chocolate mousse)
directions: Whisk together the egg yolks and granulated sugar.
Whisk in milk and cornstarch until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until boiling.
Continue to cook for 1 minute.
Whisk in broken chocolate until smooth.
Add liqueur.
Transfer to a large bowl; press with plastic and cool to room temperature.
Line a 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfinger halves.
Beat whipping cream with confectioners sugar for soft peaks.
Fold into chocolate mixture. Pour half chocolate mixture into pan.
Cover with remaining ladyfingers and add remaining half of chocolate.
Garnish with stiff whipping cream and chocolate curls.
Chill overnight.

title: never fails pie crust
directions: With fork, mix flour, shortening, sugar and salt.
In separate dish, beat vinegar, egg and water.
Mix with flour mixture.
Toss with fork.
Makes 2 double crust and 1 single (or 6).

title: banana homemade ice cream
directions: Beat the eggs well.
Add sugar, vanilla, salt, bananas and milk.
Put in 1-gallon crank freezer.
Turn until you can't turn.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Variation:
Replace 1/4 cup water with Grand Marnier.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes(can be stored 2 weeks in refrigerator)
directions: Cook and drain potatoes.
Add sour cream, salt and cream cheese.
Whip.
Add milk (leave stiffer than usual).

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine ingredients and chill until ready to serve.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix ingredients in a large mouth jar; pat dry excess juice from hot dogs.
Insert a stick in 1 end of hot dog.
Twirl hot dog in mixture until well coated.
Drop into hot oil, letting cook to a golden brown.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil; add zucchini, tomatoes and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle with parsley and Parmesan cheese.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients. Add ham for main dish meal.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
tags: loose packed frozen hash brown potatoes

title: aunt willie's old fashioned egg custard
directions: Beat eggs into sugar one at a time.
Add milk and stir well. Mix in vanilla.
Pour into unbaked 8 or 9-inch pie crust.
Bake in a 300° oven until firm (about 45 to 50 minutes).

title: pistolettes
directions: Cook ground beef, sausage and onion together.
Drain well. Cook broccoli and drain well.
Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Cut one end of roll; remove insides.
Fill with mixture.
Roll in melted margarine and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Makes about 18.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine ingredients and press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: manicotti masterpiece
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat thoroughly.
Drain meat. Put browned meat into a large mixing bowl.
Add cottage cheese. Stir well.
Add 1 cup Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Stir well.
Add shredded cheese.
Stir well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into buttered baking dish. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: white mountain icing
directions: Boil the sugar, corn syrup and water to 242°.
Beat egg whites stiff.
