Pour hot syrup mixture in a thin steady stream into egg whites.
Continue beating until it holds very stiff peaks.
Blend in vanilla.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In bowl mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, hamburg, bread crumbs, egg and onions; shape into 5 patties.
In skillet over medium heat, cook patties a few at a time until brown on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in remaining soup and mushrooms; return patties to skillet.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until done, turning occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: governor's mansion rolls
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm.
Add sugar, yeast and 1 cup of the flour.
Add oil and salt; mix well.
Add remaining flour; mix to make soft dough.
Grease dough on all sides.
Cover; let rise in a warm place, until double in size.
Place on lightly floured board; knead until smooth.
Shape into rolls, grease well and let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: party chicken breast
directions: Roll each chicken breast and wrap with one piece bacon.
Lay on a slice of dried beef.
Top with soup and sour cream mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 3 hours.

title: a world of wursts
directions: In skillet simmer kielbasa, covered, in the 1/2 cup water for 20 minutes.

title: chicken with dumplins
directions: Brown chicken in skillet in butter.
Add water, onion and seasoning.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in soup and 1 cup milk.
Add vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine biscuit mix and remainder of milk.
Drop by spoonfuls into stew.
Cook 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat after each.
Add 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup water.
Add 1 cup flour and flavor.
Add 1 cup flour.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: almond float
directions: Heat the sugar and water to make syrup.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and place in casserole dish.
Partially crush crackers and spread over mixture.
Drizzle melted margarine over crackers.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Cook lemon pudding; cover with waxed paper and chill 30 minutes.
Stir into pudding fruits and marshmallows.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding and fruit mixture.
Chill 1 hour and spoon into serving dishes.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Mix together cranberries and sugar and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Combine marshmallows and whipped topping and add to cranberry mixture. Refrigerate 2 more hours.
Combine pineapple and walnuts and add to cranberry mixture.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In saucepan, stir together tuna, mayonnaise, flour, onion and mustard.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens (about 3 to 4 minutes). Gradually stir in cheese.
Add egg noodles and tuna, mixing thoroughly.
Put into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over the top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and pour into
a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, margarine, flour and nuts.
Spread on top of sweet potato mixture.
Bake until topping is light brown at 350°, approximately 45 minutes.

title: spinach and rice casserole
directions: Saute the onion, red pepper and garlic in chicken broth until lightly browned.
Set aside.
Combine egg whites, milk, pepper and basil and stir well. To this mixture, add spinach, rice and sauteed vegetables.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into a baking dish that has been coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: frozen daiquiris
directions: In blender, mix rum, powdered sugar and lemonade.
Crush ice cubes; add small amount at a time to blender.
Mixture will be thick and slushy.
Pour into glasses.

title: nancy's tortillas
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding water gradually, until a firm dough is formed.
Form dough balls about the size of a tennis ball and roll out thin.
Cook on a hot griddle that is well oiled. Turn after first side is browned.
Turn over twice.
(Dough may be stored in refrigerator until ready to use.
Tortillas may be frozen and warmed before serving.)

title: patti's rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt, shortening, egg, milk and 3 cups flour.
Stir until mixture has a spongy texture.
Let rest for 10 minutes.
Mix in enough of the remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and divide in thirds.
Let rise for 5 minutes.
Grease 36 muffin cups.
Divide each third of dough into 36 pieces.
Shape each piece into a ball, pulling edges under to make a smooth surface.
Arrange three balls smooth side up in each muffin cup.
Cover and let rise until almost doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 3 dozen.
If cooking for two:
Freeze rolls in a plastic storage bag.
Defrost as many as needed at a moments notice.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix water, marinade and all seasonings together in a large bowl.
Add deer burger and mix well.
Allow 15 to 20 minutes for burger to soak up all seasonings.

title: applesauce cupcakes
directions: Cream the Crisco and brown sugar together. Add egg and mix well. Dissolve soda in applesauce and add to mixture. Stir in salt, cinnamon and cloves. Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Pour into cupcake pan and bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Let cool. Spread with frosting of your choice.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese; simmer.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Mix sauce with noodles.
Layer in baking pan with cheese. Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes and then 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salt water until done and then drain.
In casserole, put 1 layer of broccoli and 1 layer of bread crumbs. Repeat.
Last, beat egg, mushroom soup and cheese.
Pour this over broccoli and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lightnin' corn bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into bowl.
Add egg, milk and shortening.

title: gingerbread(recipe 100 years old)
directions: Cream bacon fat or lard with sugar until light.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Beat in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together, add alternately with buttermilk to first mixture, beating until smooth.
Pour in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Place all ingredients in medium size bowl. Beat about 2 minutes on high speed of mixer.
Pour into 9-inch greased pan. Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded Swiss or American cheese and 1/2 cup (6 strips) crisp bacon, cut in small pieces.
Push gently below surface. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Allow to set 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken piquant
directions: Mix first 10 items in bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Turn and bake another 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Serves 6.

title: lemon delight pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, sugar and 1/4 cup of the water in saucepan.
Blend in beaten egg.
Add remaining water.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Measure 1 cup filling, cover and cool completely. (Can be put in freezer ad it will be cool and ready in about 20 minutes.)
Pour remaining filling into pie shell.
Put in refrigerator.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on envelope.
Blend into the cup of cooled filling.
Spoon over filling in pie shell. Chill thoroughly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bandukes(baked potato dumplings)
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes until done.
Cool, peel and mash.
Add flour and salt.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut diagonally into small diamond shapes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Fry diced onion in butter or margarine.
When onion is tender, add cream. Pour over baked dumplings and serve.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl.
Press into pie pan.
Do not use for two crust pie.
Great for tarts, too.
Bake at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes or fill with custard and bake as for custard pie.

title: lemon bread
directions: Stir until creamy and then glaze bread while still in the pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for approximately 5 minutes.
Crush Ritz crackers and cook in melted butter.
Put above ingredients into a casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese and crackers.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss cheese ham spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts.
Beat until fluffy; chill.
Shape into a ball and coat with nuts.
Cover and chill.

title: pizza casserole i
directions: Brown meat; drain. Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Pour pizza sauce over meat. Top with cheese. Add biscuit mix, milk and eggs. Pour over meat and cheese; cover. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's cranberry salad
directions: Grind or chop cranberries in food processor.
Turn into bowl and mix in orange rind and sugar and let stand for 1 hour.

title: 4 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 4 hours before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onions, Worcestershire sauce and Accent. Form ingredients into ball.
Roll ball in chopped dried beef. Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Do not freeze.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup oleo until crumbly and press into pan or baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and ketchup in blender.
Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Mix bacon with remaining ingredients. Toss with dressing.

title: mushroom meat loaf
directions: Combine half of the can of mushroom soup with the remaining ingredients.
Shape into a loaf.
Spread remaining soup over loaf. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked fish
directions: Clean and wash fish.
Place on deep cookie sheet or in baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour Mountain Dew over top of fish.
Bake until done.
Flaky.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over lemon juice and water in small saucepan to soften.
Add sugar; stir over very low heat just until dissolved.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon rind and food coloring.
Chill 1/2 hour or until mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form when beater is raised.
Gradually add corn syrup, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold gelatin mixture into egg whites. Chill, stirring occasionally, about 1/2 hour or until thick enough to mound.
Pile lightly into pastry shell.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pecan balls
directions: Roll in
balls and bake.
Let cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: lobster chowder
directions: First, prepare to steam lobsters as follows: Combine the wine, water, garlic, lemon juice, sherry and salt in a pot large enough to hold the lobsters.
Bring to a rolling boil over high heat. Quickly place the lobsters in the pot and cover with a lid.
Cook until lobsters turn bright red (about 12 minutes).
Remove the lobsters from the pot and set aside until cool enough to handle. Now prepare ingredients for chowder.

title: toasty potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a large skillet (preferably Teflon) with enough water to barely cover the cubed potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are almost done.
Drain.

title: italarini casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Place in 3-quart casserole.
Brown beef and add to mix.
Add corn, sauces and mushrooms.
Add uncooked noodles.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.

title: watermelon punch
directions: Scoop pulp from melon and remove seeds.
Mash pulp of watermelon.
Strain.
Measure 1 gallon of juice and set aside. Combine sugar and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add to 1 gallon watermelon juice and chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Stir gently and serve over crushed ice.

title: disappearing paint
directions: Mix ingredients together and let the kids paint the patio. It disappears!

title: icebox cookies
directions: Sift together first five ingredients.
Make indentations in center and add remainder of ingredients.
Mix until sticks together well.
Make into long rolls and refrigerate.

title: pineapple icing
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil until thickened (real sticky). Put on warm cake.

title: crawfish etouffee (a-2-fay)
directions: Season crawfish tails with salt and pepper and set aside.
Melt oleo in heavy pot.
Add onions, bell peppers, garlic and celery and cook until onions are wilted, stirring constantly.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and crawfish tails.
Bring to a boil and cook over slow heat for thirty minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind up the vegies.
Add salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes until hot.
Pack in hot jars.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: deer stir-fry
directions: Cut deer into small chunks.
Salt and pepper.
Roll in flour. Fry in hot oil until done and brown on all sides.
Drain.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple and sugar.
Cut a deep slit into the thickness of each slice of bread.
This forms a pocket into which you spoon the cream cheese mixture in each slice.
Beat milk and eggs.
Dip each slice of bread quickly into the milk and eggs on each side.
Use butter to fry in frypan.
Brown both sides. Sprinkle with powdered sugar or cinnamon.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add a little cream if salad seems dry.

title: sirloin - tofu meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook onions in water until transparent and soft with all of the suggested seasonings, then set aside. Mash the block of tofu thoroughly, then mix with ground sirloin, using fork or food processor.
In separate bowl, combine juice, oats, egg whites and cooked onions.
Mix thoroughly with tofu mixture.
Divide mixture in half.
Press into two 8 x 4-inch loaf/bread pans or use small individual size loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour or until meat is cooked.
(When meat is no longer pink and juices are clear.)
Drain off any juices.
Let stand in pan about 10 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: no cook cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Heat to a boil for one minute.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and drop on wax paper.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Leave about 3 tablespoons of the bacon drippings in skillet.
Cook onion in the bacon drippings until tender.
Stir in pork and beans, brown sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire and mustard.
Put in a casserole dish and bake in the oven, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Stir.
Top with the crumbled bacon.

title: baked spinach
directions: Stir all ingredients together well. Bake for 45 minutes or until bubbly in 375° to 400° oven.

title: cherry chews
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, sugar and eggs; stir in Bisquick.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: barn yard salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Just before serving, toss in 1 large can of shoestring potatoes or serve separately.

title: taco salad
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Mold on plate and cover with onions, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: t & r's special salsa
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients gently for 45 minutes.
Then add vinegar.
Cook slowly until thick (several hours), stirring often. Keep flats and jars in pan of hot water before canning.
Fill jars.
Wipe edge of jars clean, put on lids and turn upside down overnight.

title: lime tye pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, not including whipping cream. Whip cream and fold into first mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: joann reger's candy recipe
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add sugar.
Allow two ingredients to combine.
On jelly roll pan, (line with aluminum foil and spray with Pam) lay out saltines.
Pour butter mixture on top of saltines.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Smooth chips.
Refrigerate overnight.
Enjoy!

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Boil water for pasta.
In skillet melt butter and olive oil over medium heat.
Add minced garlic clove to butter and oil.
Saute lightly, but don't allow garlic to brown.
Add shrimp.
Saute until shrimp are pink and tender.
Cook pasta.
Drain pasta and put in a large bowl.
Add shrimp and garlic butter mixture.
Toss with about 1/3 cup cheese.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix potatoes, melted butter and pepper.
Add the chopped onion, cheese, sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Mix all together.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Remove from oven and sprinkle with crushed corn flakes and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: chinese rice
directions: Brown together
ground beef and onion.
Mix with chicken rice soup,
water,
cream
of
mushroom
soup, rice, soy sauce, chopped celery
and
Worcestershire sauce.
Put in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruited rice cream
directions: Chop cherries and drain on paper towels.
Pat cherries dry and set aside.
In a heavy medium saucepan, combine milk, rice and salt over medium-low heat.
Stirring frequently to prevent mixture from scorching, cover and cook about 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender and most of milk is absorbed.
Remove from heat. Without stirring, add marshmallow and cream cheese to rice mixture; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Add sweetened condensed milk and extracts.
Stir until marshmallows melt and mixture is well blended.
Transfer to a large bowl and cool 20 minutes.
Stir cherries into rice mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and almonds. Spoon into individual serving dishes.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Yield:
about 8 cups fruited rice.

title: cheese and pasta
directions: Cook ground chuck; drain.
Cook noodles; drain.
Mix ground chuck, noodles, sour cream and the spaghetti sauce together.
Put mixture in a long baking dish.
Put Mozzarella cheese over mixture.
Bake at 350°until cheese is melted well.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 10 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes, or longer as necessary.

title: hawaiian pork(sweet and sour)
directions: Brown pork in Crisco.
Add water; cover and cook 1 hour over low heat.
Combine cornstarch, salt, sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce in a saucepan and cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over hot pork.
Allow to stand 10 minutes.
Stir in green pepper, onion and pineapple. Cook about 5 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Put salt into water and bring to boil.
Add macaroni.
Use just amount of water that when macaroni is done it won't have to be drained.
Watch closely.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: daves oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine bran, nuts, fruit and baking powder. Stir in honey, brown sugar or molasses. Mix egg whites, milk and oil together and blend in with mix. Line muffin pans with paper cups and pour in batter. Bake 20 to 30 minutes. Test with toothpick for doneness. Store in plastic bag and refrigerate.

title: sandies(cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, water and flour.
Mix well.
Add chopped pecans.
Form small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 20 minutes or until brown.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: crazy cake
directions: Place sugar and flour in large bowl.
In saucepan, bring to boil oleo, water and cocoa.
Pour over sugar and flour, beat well. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a well buttered deep cookie sheet or 9 x 13 baking pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.
Five minutes before cake is done, cook icing to a boil.

title: marcie's king ranch chicken
directions: Stew chicken with pepper, salt and bay leaf.
Bone and cut in bite size pieces.
Cook green pepper and onions in butter until tender.
Stir in soups and Ro-Tel.
Simmer about 15 minutes until well blended.
Add chicken to soup mix.
Arrange tortilla chips in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour soup mix on top of chips. Put cheese on top and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until soft.
Mash until smooth, then add eggs, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven or until crust is browned.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Boil chicken in a small amount of water until done.
Chop chicken and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, picante sauce and onion.
Layer half of tortillas, chicken and soup mixture and cheese in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, coated with Pam.
Layer second half.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour and dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Slice when cooled.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in hot skillet, to which 3 tablespoons cooking oil has been added, for 30 minutes at 350° (or spray with Pam).

title: cranberry conserve
directions: Cook berries in cold water.
Put through strainer.
Add boiling water.
Add raisins, chopped orange and sugar. Simmer for 20 minutes. Add nut meats.
Store in refrigerator or pour into sterilized jars and seal with wax when cool.

title: easy salmon dill mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice; chill until thickened.
Mix salmon with sour cream, mayonnaise, onion and dill.
Blend into gelatin.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold.
Serve with crisp salad greens.
Garnish with fresh dill and thinly sliced cucumbers or lemon wedges, if desired.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until half done.
Meanwhile, in a bowl open tuna and flake apart.
Drain noodles.
In large bowl stir onion, noodles and tuna and mushroom soup together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a casserole dish.
Pour noodle mix in.
Sprinkle with crumbs or potato chips.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup melted margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Mix well and put into casserole dish.
Mix remaining oleo with the crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip mint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
Cream together butter or margarine and sugars with an electric mixer at high speed.
Beat in egg.
Stir in vanilla and peppermint extracts.
Sift together dry ingredients and add this to the butter mixture, along with the chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir until well combined.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Make rice as instructed; cool.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Prepare at least 4 to 6 hours in advance.

title: baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine bread crumbs, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese and lemon zest. Rinse fillets gently and pat dry. Rub fillets with oil; dip in bread crumbs, coating each side. Bake 15 to 20 minutes, uncovered, until done. Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.

title: dawson's leg of lamb
directions: Trim the fat and skin from the leg of lamb.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Place lamb in baking pan.
Top with mixture.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes on each side.
Baste with sauce.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Cook Crisco, margarine, cocoa and water in microwave until boiling, then add vanilla, soda, buttermilk, sugar and eggs.
Mix. Put in greased oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix with chicken soup, cheese and chicken.
Spread in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cook macaroni and drain.
Layer 1/3 macaroni, sprinkle lightly salt and pepper and 1/3 of cheese.
Dotting with slivers of butter; repeat twice more.
Pour milk over all.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buche de noel(yield: 10-12 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Line with a piece of waxed paper 1/2-inch smaller than the pan; butter the paper.

title: minnesota cucumbers
directions: Combine cucumbers, green pepper, onion, celery seed and salt in bowl; mix well.
Stir sugar into vinegar in small bowl until dissolved.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
May store in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: special k cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, coconut, walnut meats and raisins; mix well.
Stir in Special K.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 6 dozen (1 1/2-inch diameter) cookies.

title: light 'n' luscious trifle
directions: In a large bowl, toss the honeydew and strawberries with fruit spread; set aside. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Add sour cream; mix well. Fold in whipped topping and cake. Drain juice from fruit mixture. In a trifle dish or deep salad bowl, layer a third of the fruit, a third of the cake mixture and a third of the chocolate. Repeat layers twice. Serve immediately.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine milk, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, vanilla and eggs. Beat well.
Pour into freezer.
Use regular milk to fill to fill line.
Turn freezer until frozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Stir together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef parma style
directions: Place meat between sheets of wax paper. Pound with heavy skillet on hard surface until quite thin.
Cut into serving size pieces.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients; put into the unbaked pastry. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: iced tea
directions: Microwave first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute, then add sugar (more or less to taste).
Add to ice cubes and cold water to make one gallon.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk until smooth. Add Eagle Brand, sour cream, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth.

title: minute fudge icing
directions: Bring to boil first 5 ingredients, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Beat until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until thick. If too thick, add 1 tablespoon of cream.

title: french onion rings
directions: Sift flour and salt in a bowl.
Add milk, oil and egg.
Beat until smooth.
Cut onion into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings.
Dip each ring into batter.
Drain excess batter.
Drop rings into heated shortening (375°).
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until it crumbs like meal.
Mix the next 3 ingredients with egg and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Pour the second mixture into greased and floured sheet pan.
Sprinkle topping (first mixture) over.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: easy deviled eggs
directions: Split eggs lengthwise and set on plate. Combine yolks and remaining ingredients except paprika. Spoon mixture into whites and sprinkle with paprika.

title: biscochitos(mexican cookies)
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream lard with sugar and anise seed until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in flour and brandy until well blended.
Turn dough out on floured board and pat or roll to 1/4 or 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes.
Dust with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° or until browned.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup dry cake mix.
In a large bowl, combine remaining cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Mix well.
Pat into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine reserved cake mix, pumpkin, sugar, 2 eggs, peel and dash of salt.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over partially baked layer. Top with nuts. Bake at 350° until set (15 to 20 minutes). Cool. Cut into bars. Refrigerate.
Makes 32 bars.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Mix 1st 4 ingredients in a deep bowl.
Add hot water.
Beat to stiff peaks.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and fluff together.
Put into a serving bowl and dip fruit.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form loaf.
Place in shallow pan and start baking at 350° while combining the sauce ingredients.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, barbecue sauce and brown sugar. Simmer 10 minutes.

title: oblick
directions: If color is desired, add to water, then combine with cornstarch.
Try adding more or less of each ingredient.
Punch it, it's hard!
Stick your finger in it and stir slowly, it's soft!

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
In small bowl, beat cheese, margarine and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened milk, then egg and vanilla until smooth.
Pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan. Cool.
Drizzle with chocolate glaze.

title: spice cake
directions: Cook 2 cups raisins for 20 minutes in 2 cups water. Put 1 teaspoon soda in 1 cup raisin water. Add 3 cups flour and 1/2 cup walnuts. Blend all together! Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: treasure cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl mix graham cracker crumbs, flour and baking powder.
In a large bowl mix milk and margarine until smooth.
Add flour mixture, mix well.
Stir in coconut and chips. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Store at room temperature.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with condensed milk just until blended.
Add lime juice and beat until mixture thickens slightly.
Pour into baked and cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Whip cream and fold in sugar.
Spread over pie filling, making sure whipped cream touches pastry all around.
Return to refrigerator and chill several hours or overnight before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream the cheese and butter. Blend in all ingredients except olives.
Mold a tablespoonful of cheese mixture around each olive.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix together cheese, sour cream and soup.
Coat Tater Tots with cheese mixture, then add butter and onions.
You may save some cheese to sprinkle over the top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry apple crisp
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex with Pam.
Spread bottom with Quaker honey-nut toasted oatmeal dry cereal.
Layer in cut up apples (about 4) and the cranberries.
Sprinkle with the nutmeg and cinnamon mixed with the sugar.
Add more cereal on top as pan will allow.
Doll up with brown sugar and butter.
Sprinkle on 3 tablespoons water and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: corn custard with cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl except cheese.
Put part of cheese in mixture.
Place in greased baking dish.
Arrange remainder of cheese on top of mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer to 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
This makes a great potluck dish; travels well and is quickly eaten.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Bring chicken broth and water to a boil.
Add onion, carrot and broccoli; cook until broccoli begins to get tender.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Mix flour and cold water thoroughly to make thickening.
Slowly stir into soup.
Stir in cheeses, then milk. Stir frequently.
Do not return to boil.
Serve hot!

title: pudding cake and lemon sauce
directions: Whiz milk, vanilla and dates.
Combine this with bread crumbs (tear bread into dry blender and whiz lightly, 2 slices at a time), 1/2 cup pineapple and juice, carrots, walnuts and raisins.
Spoon lightly into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 60 minutes.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute the onion and mushrooms in some of the oleo until onion is clear.
Put in a casserole dish
with the remaining ingredients.
The mixture will be "soupy" before baking. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes with a lid, then 15 minutes without a lid.

title: shrimp and artichoke hearts
directions: Add onion to melted butter; saute.
Stir in flour until blended.
Add milk to mushroom liquid to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Gradually add to butter-flour mixture.
Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, shrimp and mushrooms.
Arrange artichokes in bottom of buttered casserole, 8-inch size.
Pour shrimp sauce over artichokes.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.

title: liver sausage
directions: Cook head meat, hearts, trimmings, etc. until bones can be removed easily.
When cooked, grind all the meat through grinder. Remove all blood vessels from hog liver and cut liver deeply with knife and scald in boiling water for about 10 minutes.
Grind.
Use about 8 pounds head meat to 1 1/2 to 2 pounds liver.
Add enough liquid from ground meat to make a soft texture.
Add cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Four parts meat, 3 parts liquid and 1 part cereal by weight.
Can in jars or freeze.
Slice and fry in skillet.
Omit liver if desired.

title: irish apple cake
directions: Cream the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl. Combine with dry ingredients and mix well. Add nuts and apples. Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle chips over it and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hot bacon dressing for lettuce or endive
directions: Cut bacon in 1-inch pieces and brown.
Remove from pan and drain.
To bacon fat, add vinegar, water and sugar and heat to boiling.
Beat egg in bowl and stir into hot mixture slowly.
